WEBVTT

1
00:00:24.793 --> 00:00:27.543
[Music plays Mozart's
Piano Concerto No. 23]

2
00:00:28.213 --> 00:00:30.383
[Elegant. melancholic piano notes]

3
00:01:13.543 --> 00:01:16.173
[Delicate. melancholic
string instruments join]

4
00:01:19.673 --> 00:01:21.843
[Sizzling]

5
00:01:33.883 --> 00:01:34.883
Yeah...

6
00:01:35.713 --> 00:01:37.479
Come on. fall!

7
00:01:37.503 --> 00:01:39.769
[Birds chirp]

8
00:01:39.793 --> 00:01:42.253
[Wind rustles]

9
00:01:53.253 --> 00:01:55.253
[Music continues]

10
00:01:55.963 --> 00:01:58.019
They must really like you.

11
00:01:58.043 --> 00:01:59.519
Sending you expensive eel.

12
00:01:59.543 --> 00:02:00.963
It's not that they like me.

13
00:02:01.503 --> 00:02:03.729
They're going to work me even harder.

14
00:02:03.753 --> 00:02:05.253
[Miri] Those Americans too

15
00:02:05.343 --> 00:02:08.343
must know that eels
make men perform better.

16
00:02:09.633 --> 00:02:12.463
They even sent it on your birthday.

17
00:02:15.343 --> 00:02:16.439
The kids will hear!

18
00:02:16.463 --> 00:02:17.519
[He groans]

19
00:02:17.543 --> 00:02:21.019
- [Man-su] I need eel! Eel!
- [Low cello note]

20
00:02:21.043 --> 00:02:23.439
- Come and eat!
- [Music brightens]

21
00:02:23.463 --> 00:02:27.519
Dad sweated in the heat grilling these.

22
00:02:27.543 --> 00:02:28.793
I'll go.

23
00:02:35.593 --> 00:02:36.593
A snake?

24
00:02:37.543 --> 00:02:39.019
Snakes don't taste this good!

25
00:02:39.043 --> 00:02:42.229
Dad's company sent it.
for doing a good job.

26
00:02:42.253 --> 00:02:43.633
It's not even a holiday.

27
00:02:44.543 --> 00:02:46.423
[Boy] Couldn't they give us beef?

28
00:02:47.673 --> 00:02:48.673
Ri-one.

29
00:02:49.253 --> 00:02:50.503
Dinner.

30
00:02:53.093 --> 00:02:55.673
Come on. Let's eat.

31
00:02:57.293 --> 00:02:58.963
Let the cello take a nap.

32
00:03:00.253 --> 00:03:01.293
[Horse neighs nearby]

33
00:03:01.383 --> 00:03:03.149
[Piano Concerto No. 23
continues on speaker]

34
00:03:03.173 --> 00:03:04.293
[Woman] What's this?

35
00:03:13.883 --> 00:03:16.543
Honey!

36
00:03:19.543 --> 00:03:21.633
Must've been expensive!

37
00:03:22.843 --> 00:03:25.923
Well. I can afford decent dance shoes.

38
00:03:26.503 --> 00:03:28.729
- Aren't Mom's shoes pretty?
- Eat up.

39
00:03:28.753 --> 00:03:30.423
[Woman squeals with joy]

40
00:03:32.133 --> 00:03:34.093
[Woman] I'll be able to dance so well
in these.

41
00:03:37.383 --> 00:03:40.479
They say not to gift shoes to your lover.

42
00:03:40.503 --> 00:03:42.229
- [Boy] Why?
- [Ri-one] Why?

43
00:03:42.253 --> 00:03:44.229
'Cause they might run away in them.

44
00:03:44.253 --> 00:03:45.439
[Man chuckles. softly]

45
00:03:45.463 --> 00:03:48.173
Seems your dad is confident.

46
00:03:49.883 --> 00:03:50.923
Come on.

47
00:03:52.003 --> 00:03:53.923
We need to practice when we can.

48
00:03:55.713 --> 00:03:57.689
Ready. start!

49
00:03:57.713 --> 00:03:59.439
- One two three.
- [Dog barks]

50
00:03:59.463 --> 00:04:03.543
two two three. three two three...

51
00:04:05.343 --> 00:04:07.293
[Woman laughs]

52
00:04:11.253 --> 00:04:13.423
[Music continues]

53
00:04:19.343 --> 00:04:21.133
[She hums in refusal. muted]

54
00:04:28.633 --> 00:04:31.399
THANKS FOR YOUR HARD WORK
AND YEARS OF DEDICATION TO SOLAR PAPER.

55
00:04:31.423 --> 00:04:33.423
Damned paper.

56
00:04:34.503 --> 00:04:36.269
Honey. come here.

57
00:04:36.293 --> 00:04:37.293
Why?

58
00:04:39.133 --> 00:04:40.593
Come on.

59
00:04:41.543 --> 00:04:42.729
Come on. Ri-one.

60
00:04:42.753 --> 00:04:44.713
[He sighs]

61
00:04:45.503 --> 00:04:51.543
RI-TWO SI-TWO

62
00:04:55.593 --> 00:04:56.843
Just three minutes more.

63
00:04:57.713 --> 00:04:59.213
- [She grunts]
- One minute.

64
00:05:07.753 --> 00:05:09.213
Know what I'm feeling now?

65
00:05:13.133 --> 00:05:14.899
I've got it all.

66
00:05:14.923 --> 00:05:17.093
[Music continues]

67
00:05:31.253 --> 00:05:34.253
[Music fades.
transitions into loud rumble]

68
00:05:50.883 --> 00:05:55.503
[Man-su] <i>You people bought Solar Paper.
where I devoted 25 years of my life.</i>

69
00:05:56.173 --> 00:05:58.019
<i>But as soon as you take over. you say</i>

70
00:05:58.043 --> 00:06:00.343
<i>you'll cut 20% of the production line?</i>

71
00:06:01.173 --> 00:06:03.463
<i>And you ask for a list of names to fire?</i>

72
00:06:04.293 --> 00:06:07.173
<i>Names of veterans
who taught me their craft?</i>

73
00:06:08.133 --> 00:06:10.713
<i>Names of young men
who came of age in this factory?</i>

74
00:06:11.883 --> 00:06:14.899
<i>Innocent workers who lovingly
cared for these machines.</i>

75
00:06:14.923 --> 00:06:18.133
<i>you want me to point a gun at their heads?</i>

76
00:06:19.423 --> 00:06:20.543
<i>I can't do it.</i>

77
00:06:20.633 --> 00:06:22.189
[Machinery whirs. loudly]

78
00:06:22.213 --> 00:06:24.253
<i>Guns are meant to be aimed
at one's enemies!</i>

79
00:06:24.343 --> 00:06:25.399
STOP! THINK! ACT!

80
00:06:25.423 --> 00:06:28.383
<i>I cannot give you that list.</i>

81
00:06:30.883 --> 00:06:32.793
<i>You Americans say</i>

82
00:06:32.883 --> 00:06:34.793
to be fired is to be 'axed'?

83
00:06:35.633 --> 00:06:37.543
Know what we say in Korea?

84
00:06:37.633 --> 00:06:39.293
Off with your head!

85
00:06:39.383 --> 00:06:41.213
So being fired

86
00:06:42.253 --> 00:06:46.229
is having your head chopped
clear off with an axe!

87
00:06:46.253 --> 00:06:48.503
[Loud thudding and whirring]

88
00:06:51.633 --> 00:06:52.689
JOB FOR LIFE.
OLD SHOES

89
00:06:52.713 --> 00:06:55.593
"If you don't start a union.
we guarantee a job for life."

90
00:06:56.173 --> 00:07:00.899
[He strains his voice] That beautiful
tradition... tossed out like old shoes!

91
00:07:00.923 --> 00:07:02.899
To you Americans...!

92
00:07:02.923 --> 00:07:04.093
Damn. my throat.

93
00:07:04.673 --> 00:07:07.003
I said to do this in the warehouse.

94
00:07:07.093 --> 00:07:09.399
All because you wanted to smoke.

95
00:07:09.423 --> 00:07:10.479
Quit. dammit!

96
00:07:10.503 --> 00:07:13.189
You put so much work into this.

97
00:07:13.213 --> 00:07:14.793
He could've said. forget it.

98
00:07:14.883 --> 00:07:18.649
- But he acts like it's his job at stake.
- It is!

99
00:07:18.673 --> 00:07:21.003
If you guys are fired.
who will I work with?

100
00:07:21.093 --> 00:07:22.793
Real sense of humanity.

101
00:07:23.343 --> 00:07:24.343
[He mumbles] Damn.

102
00:07:26.633 --> 00:07:28.043
- [Dissonant squeal]
- Stop!

103
00:07:28.593 --> 00:07:30.843
[Men speak indistinctly in English]

104
00:07:32.293 --> 00:07:34.503
[Subtle. unsettling music]

105
00:07:36.003 --> 00:07:37.399
Hello. sir.

106
00:07:37.423 --> 00:07:38.939
{\an8}[In English] He wants to say something.

107
00:07:38.963 --> 00:07:41.293
[Man speaks in Korean.
interpreter in English] In America.

108
00:07:41.383 --> 00:07:43.923
when you get fired. you say.
"you got axed".

109
00:07:44.463 --> 00:07:46.343
{\an8}[In English] I'm sorry.
there's no other choice.

110
00:07:46.593 --> 00:07:49.189
- You know what we say in Korea?
- [In Korean] Off with your head!

111
00:07:49.213 --> 00:07:51.343
- So to be fired...
- [Worker] Give back the helmet!

112
00:07:51.463 --> 00:07:53.753
is to chop your head clear off!

113
00:07:53.843 --> 00:07:54.843
[Worker] Wait!

114
00:07:56.133 --> 00:07:58.479
What'll he do with that helmet?

115
00:07:58.503 --> 00:08:00.543
[Music continues]

116
00:08:01.133 --> 00:08:02.713
[He exhales. annoyed]

117
00:08:05.383 --> 00:08:08.173
They didn't... give you the eel. did they?

118
00:08:13.173 --> 00:08:14.503
No way. right?

119
00:08:17.963 --> 00:08:20.093
[Music concludes. resonates]

120
00:08:20.673 --> 00:08:22.149
[Silence]

121
00:08:22.173 --> 00:08:23.269
Honey.

122
00:08:23.293 --> 00:08:24.793
[Chirping interrupts silence]

123
00:08:24.883 --> 00:08:26.003
What?

124
00:08:26.093 --> 00:08:28.019
You said you'd say something.

125
00:08:28.043 --> 00:08:30.043
[Dog pants]

126
00:08:30.133 --> 00:08:31.229
I forgot.

127
00:08:31.253 --> 00:08:32.793
[Woman] Aren't you going to work?

128
00:08:32.883 --> 00:08:33.883
Right. right.

129
00:08:34.503 --> 00:08:35.503
That's right.

130
00:08:37.173 --> 00:08:38.753
Si-two. Ri-two. house!

131
00:08:39.673 --> 00:08:40.883
[Woman] Study hard.

132
00:08:43.463 --> 00:08:45.479
- Ri-one. let's go.
- Ri-one!

133
00:08:45.503 --> 00:08:47.673
Have a good day.

134
00:08:53.343 --> 00:08:54.633
Good luck!

135
00:08:56.793 --> 00:08:59.133
I slaved for 25 years!

136
00:09:00.003 --> 00:09:01.463
[He grunts]

137
00:09:07.423 --> 00:09:08.503
Deep breaths.

138
00:09:08.593 --> 00:09:10.793
[She breathes heavily]

139
00:09:12.753 --> 00:09:15.253
[Heavy breathing continues]

140
00:09:22.633 --> 00:09:25.149
[Subtle. unsettling music]

141
00:09:25.173 --> 00:09:27.149
- [Instructor] <i>I am...</i>
- [Workers] <i>I am...</i>

142
00:09:27.173 --> 00:09:28.253
[Instructor] A good person.

143
00:09:28.343 --> 00:09:29.939
A good person.

144
00:09:29.963 --> 00:09:31.229
[Instructor] Man-su!

145
00:09:31.253 --> 00:09:32.253
person.

146
00:09:32.343 --> 00:09:34.503
- [Instructor] Losing my job...
- Losing my job...

147
00:09:34.593 --> 00:09:36.874
- [Instructor] Losing my job!
- [Workers] Losing my job...

148
00:09:37.633 --> 00:09:40.979
[Instructor] is not my choice!

149
00:09:41.003 --> 00:09:43.133
[Workers repeat]

150
00:09:44.173 --> 00:09:47.019
- [Instructor] My loving family...
- [Workers] My loving family...

151
00:09:47.043 --> 00:09:48.673
[Instructor] My loving family...

152
00:09:49.713 --> 00:09:52.963
will support me fully
as I seek new opportunities.

153
00:09:53.593 --> 00:09:57.593
as I seek new opportunities.

154
00:09:58.253 --> 00:10:02.503
[Man-su's voice becomes distinct]
My loving family will support me fully

155
00:10:02.593 --> 00:10:04.543
as I seek new opportunities.

156
00:10:06.423 --> 00:10:08.343
[Music continues]

157
00:10:10.793 --> 00:10:12.213
[Woman] <i>Honey.</i>

158
00:10:13.043 --> 00:10:14.519
Can you put in earphones?

159
00:10:14.543 --> 00:10:15.793
[Woman] <i>Just a sec.</i>

160
00:10:17.213 --> 00:10:18.713
HIRED IN THREE MONTHS

161
00:10:19.343 --> 00:10:21.189
[Effort grunts. playful yelling]

162
00:10:21.213 --> 00:10:22.939
[She exclaims. softly]

163
00:10:22.963 --> 00:10:26.423
So you must've had sleepless nights?

164
00:10:30.293 --> 00:10:31.343
Are you crying?

165
00:10:32.383 --> 00:10:34.019
[Tennis balls thud]

166
00:10:34.043 --> 00:10:38.843
Where's that brave bachelor
who proposed to a single mom?

167
00:10:39.633 --> 00:10:43.673
I made a new start. you can too.

168
00:10:45.003 --> 00:10:46.479
Sure you can!

169
00:10:46.503 --> 00:10:49.793
- Take all your hopes and dreams.
- [Indistinct murmur]

170
00:10:49.883 --> 00:10:53.133
- <i>and recite your own incantation.</i>
- [Sorrowful string music]

171
00:10:53.793 --> 00:10:54.793
<i>Ready?</i>

172
00:10:54.883 --> 00:10:56.439
Go!

173
00:10:56.463 --> 00:10:57.793
[Loud murmur]

174
00:10:59.253 --> 00:11:00.293
[Man-su] <i>A new start...</i>

175
00:11:00.383 --> 00:11:02.229
<i>A new start... A new start...</i>

176
00:11:02.253 --> 00:11:03.253
<i>A new start.</i>

177
00:11:03.343 --> 00:11:04.673
A new start.

178
00:11:05.543 --> 00:11:06.883
I'm head of a family.

179
00:11:08.383 --> 00:11:09.593
I'll be born again.

180
00:11:11.043 --> 00:11:14.503
To put food in my family's mouths...

181
00:11:15.343 --> 00:11:16.843
<i>there's nothing I won't do.</i>

182
00:11:17.543 --> 00:11:19.229
[Music continues]

183
00:11:19.253 --> 00:11:20.593
In three months.

184
00:11:22.633 --> 00:11:24.133
I'll get hired again!

185
00:11:25.383 --> 00:11:26.383
[He shouts. determined]

186
00:11:28.293 --> 00:11:29.843
[Yelling. muffled] I feel great!

187
00:11:30.793 --> 00:11:32.503
[Music concludes;
He groans]

188
00:11:32.593 --> 00:11:35.003
3 MONTHS LATER

189
00:11:35.093 --> 00:11:38.253
- 13 MONTHS LATER
- [Message alert]

190
00:11:38.343 --> 00:11:40.399
Hi Namgu. I know.

191
00:11:40.423 --> 00:11:41.503
Today at five o'clock.

192
00:11:41.593 --> 00:11:43.753
[Namgu] <i>My boss is really curious
about you.</i>

193
00:11:44.293 --> 00:11:48.229
<i>Sorry to ask so suddenly.
but can you come at noon?</i>

194
00:11:48.253 --> 00:11:49.793
Listen. I'm...

195
00:11:50.843 --> 00:11:54.189
- at the retail store. with my wife.
- [Repetitive beeps in background]

196
00:11:54.213 --> 00:11:58.399
[Namgu] <i>The boss suddenly booked
a 5pm flight back to China.</i>

197
00:11:58.423 --> 00:12:01.543
- <i>Too much to ask?</i>
- No. no. hold on. Wait.

198
00:12:01.673 --> 00:12:04.503
I'll plead with my wife.

199
00:12:04.593 --> 00:12:05.649
[Namgu] <i>That's right.</i>

200
00:12:05.673 --> 00:12:08.189
<i>Come over now.</i>

201
00:12:08.213 --> 00:12:12.503
<i>But there's a question he always asks.
"What's your weak point?"</i>

202
00:12:12.593 --> 00:12:13.649
[Man-su] <i>Weak point?</i>

203
00:12:13.673 --> 00:12:18.229
[Namgu] <i>It's a crucial-utely
sensitive issue. okay?</i>

204
00:12:18.253 --> 00:12:19.633
[Man-su] <i>Okay. thanks!</i>

205
00:12:37.213 --> 00:12:39.213
[Indistinct chatter]

206
00:12:41.673 --> 00:12:42.729
[Woman] Weak point?

207
00:12:42.753 --> 00:12:45.753
[Man-su] <i>Sorry. I know it's absolutely
impossible to answer.</i>

208
00:12:45.843 --> 00:12:47.503
<i>What's my weak point?</i>

209
00:12:47.593 --> 00:12:51.769
What do you think?
You love plants too much.

210
00:12:51.793 --> 00:12:53.253
You're a vegetable.

211
00:12:54.133 --> 00:12:55.979
[Man-su] <i>Last night
you called me an animal.</i>

212
00:12:56.003 --> 00:12:57.713
[She chuckles]

213
00:12:58.883 --> 00:13:01.793
- <i>Namgu gave me this awesome tip.</i>
- [Dog pants]

214
00:13:02.503 --> 00:13:04.519
- MORTGAGE DEFAULT WARNING
- [Sparse. somber notes]

215
00:13:04.543 --> 00:13:07.043
<i>If only I can explain
my weak point well.</i>

216
00:13:07.133 --> 00:13:09.713
- <i>It's a crucial-utely sensitive issue.</i>
- [Music builds]

217
00:13:11.093 --> 00:13:15.503
[Interviewer] If you're hired. you'll work
under your former subordinate Namgu.

218
00:13:15.593 --> 00:13:17.769
- Tell us how you feel about that.
- [Music concludes]

219
00:13:17.793 --> 00:13:19.729
I was a manager. true.

220
00:13:19.753 --> 00:13:23.753
but I've always considered
myself to be blue collar.

221
00:13:26.423 --> 00:13:28.253
So. in that respect...

222
00:13:28.343 --> 00:13:31.479
I don't think you understood
the question.

223
00:13:31.503 --> 00:13:32.633
[Interpreter mumbles]

224
00:13:33.213 --> 00:13:34.269
Namgu...

225
00:13:34.293 --> 00:13:37.383
No. of course I understand.
my point is...

226
00:13:37.963 --> 00:13:41.753
Namgu came to Papyrus first.
so you'll learn from him. right?

227
00:13:41.843 --> 00:13:43.133
Of course!

228
00:13:44.093 --> 00:13:45.503
I am always learning.

229
00:13:46.133 --> 00:13:49.843
I got hired as soon as
I graduated from high school.

230
00:13:50.503 --> 00:13:54.939
But even while working.
I earned a chemistry degree.

231
00:13:54.963 --> 00:13:58.003
Of course. that was at
a distance university.

232
00:13:58.093 --> 00:13:59.343
[Interpreter mumbles]

233
00:14:01.463 --> 00:14:06.293
Of course after that too.
I kept... learning.

234
00:14:06.383 --> 00:14:09.343
And of course. safety management.

235
00:14:10.293 --> 00:14:16.229
When I received the 2019
'Pulp Man of the Year'.

236
00:14:16.253 --> 00:14:19.963
it was that aspect
that they singled out in my record.

237
00:14:20.633 --> 00:14:23.293
And that same year.

238
00:14:23.383 --> 00:14:26.093
I finally bought my own home.

239
00:14:26.883 --> 00:14:30.003
The very house I was born in.

240
00:14:30.093 --> 00:14:31.463
Of course...

241
00:14:32.173 --> 00:14:34.439
I'm saying "of course" too much. aren't I?

242
00:14:34.463 --> 00:14:35.923
[He chuckles]

243
00:14:37.093 --> 00:14:40.593
It's not so much because I'm nervous.

244
00:14:41.213 --> 00:14:45.293
but... self-confidence? Assurance?
That's what it is.

245
00:14:45.843 --> 00:14:47.633
Of course!

246
00:14:50.213 --> 00:14:51.793
[He speaks in Chinese]

247
00:14:51.883 --> 00:14:55.503
[Interpreter. in Korean] Could you
tell me about your weak point?

248
00:14:58.633 --> 00:14:59.939
[He inhales deeply]

249
00:14:59.963 --> 00:15:01.003
No.

250
00:15:05.003 --> 00:15:06.753
[Interpreter whispers]

251
00:15:07.423 --> 00:15:11.923
Is the one thing I can't say.
that's my biggest weak point!

252
00:15:17.593 --> 00:15:19.689
Have you looked into Moon Paper?

253
00:15:19.713 --> 00:15:20.713
Moon?

254
00:15:21.383 --> 00:15:26.753
They say Moon Paper has cracked
the Japanese market. look into it.

255
00:15:26.843 --> 00:15:30.189
Pacific Paper is restructuring
this winter. too.

256
00:15:30.213 --> 00:15:31.213
[Man-su] Really?

257
00:15:31.843 --> 00:15:33.253
Go to a dentist. will you?

258
00:15:34.253 --> 00:15:35.423
Just go. okay?

259
00:15:36.633 --> 00:15:38.939
If you get hired.
you'll be too busy to go.

260
00:15:38.963 --> 00:15:40.293
No. I'm fine.

261
00:15:40.383 --> 00:15:42.519
There's that pigheadedness of yours!

262
00:15:42.543 --> 00:15:43.793
[Low. indistinct murmur]

263
00:15:43.883 --> 00:15:47.793
Anyway. get hired
before winter. okay?

264
00:15:47.883 --> 00:15:49.713
The company will call you soon.

265
00:15:50.843 --> 00:15:51.899
Thanks.

266
00:15:51.923 --> 00:15:53.149
[Man murmurs]

267
00:15:53.173 --> 00:15:55.713
Don't forget. Moon Paper!

268
00:15:57.383 --> 00:15:59.753
[Man] I'm a man. I'm a good person.

269
00:16:01.173 --> 00:16:03.769
{\an8}<i>Founded by legendary paper man
Moon Changho.</i>

270
00:16:03.793 --> 00:16:05.439
{\an8}CHOI SUN-CHUL.
LINE MANAGER AT MOON PAPER

271
00:16:05.463 --> 00:16:06.793
{\an8}<i>- Moon Paper is...
- Mr Choi!</i>

272
00:16:06.883 --> 00:16:07.883
{\an8}<i>Yes?</i>

273
00:16:08.003 --> 00:16:11.479
{\an8}<i>We agreed to talk about
how paper is made.</i>

274
00:16:11.503 --> 00:16:13.189
{\an8}<i>- That's what I'm...
- Leave the promotion</i>

275
00:16:13.213 --> 00:16:14.293
{\an8}<i>to the company channel.</i>

276
00:16:14.383 --> 00:16:16.543
- [Playful melody]
- <i>Six hours 17 minutes later.</i>

277
00:16:16.633 --> 00:16:21.253
{\an8}<i>Many people think paper companies
mindlessly raze entire forests. right?</i>

278
00:16:21.343 --> 00:16:22.503
{\an8}<i>That's not true.</i>

279
00:16:22.593 --> 00:16:25.093
[Sparse. somber piano music]

280
00:16:35.343 --> 00:16:37.633
[Music turns intriguing]

281
00:16:52.293 --> 00:16:54.213
[Branches creak]

282
00:16:58.753 --> 00:17:00.149
[He sighs]

283
00:17:00.173 --> 00:17:01.543
[He clicks his tongue]

284
00:17:03.923 --> 00:17:04.963
[He mouths] What?

285
00:17:07.173 --> 00:17:08.399
[Music concludes]

286
00:17:08.423 --> 00:17:10.043
[Woman] First. the good news.

287
00:17:10.133 --> 00:17:12.649
- I got a part-time job.
- [Faint. unsettling tone]

288
00:17:12.673 --> 00:17:14.689
Mom's going out to work now!

289
00:17:14.713 --> 00:17:17.543
[Boy] You always blamed us
for killing your career.

290
00:17:17.633 --> 00:17:19.899
Congrats. Mom!

291
00:17:19.923 --> 00:17:21.519
[Woman] Thanks.

292
00:17:21.543 --> 00:17:23.939
Where? A dental clinic?

293
00:17:23.963 --> 00:17:27.439
- Dr Oh Chin-ho.
- Dr Ouch In-ho?

294
00:17:27.463 --> 00:17:29.189
- No jokes allowed.
- [Tone halts]

295
00:17:29.213 --> 00:17:32.883
I'd like us all to face the fact
we're in a crisis.

296
00:17:33.543 --> 00:17:37.003
Refrain from the listed activities
until Dad finds work.

297
00:17:37.093 --> 00:17:40.253
Except for Ri-one's lessons.
anything non-essential must go.

298
00:17:41.253 --> 00:17:43.229
- For example...
- For example. meat in the soup?

299
00:17:43.253 --> 00:17:46.189
There is some. look harder.

300
00:17:46.213 --> 00:17:48.293
[Dog barks in the distance]

301
00:17:48.383 --> 00:17:49.423
For example.

302
00:17:50.003 --> 00:17:51.633
<i>my car.</i>

303
00:17:52.213 --> 00:17:54.383
We'll trade your car
for something smaller.

304
00:17:56.843 --> 00:17:59.003
And our house.

305
00:17:59.093 --> 00:18:01.043
[Sad. delicate music]

306
00:18:02.133 --> 00:18:04.093
[All] Huh?

307
00:18:04.843 --> 00:18:09.399
If we sell the house. we can pay off
our loans and rent an apartment.

308
00:18:09.423 --> 00:18:11.543
[Music continues]

309
00:18:11.633 --> 00:18:14.189
You said you'd find work in three months.

310
00:18:14.213 --> 00:18:18.689
So we kept living as usual.
dipping into your severance pay.

311
00:18:18.713 --> 00:18:21.003
Now that's run dry.

312
00:18:27.213 --> 00:18:30.043
- HOUSE FORECLOSURE IN THREE MONTHS
- [Man-su breathes shakily]

313
00:18:30.133 --> 00:18:31.253
[Man-su] Honey.

314
00:18:32.843 --> 00:18:34.043
This house...

315
00:18:35.213 --> 00:18:36.713
[Vocal croaking]

316
00:18:38.253 --> 00:18:40.793
I have so many childhood memories
in this home.

317
00:18:42.043 --> 00:18:46.729
After turning nine.
I moved every ten months on average.

318
00:18:46.753 --> 00:18:48.923
I worked so hard to buy back this home.

319
00:18:50.093 --> 00:18:51.293
I mean. we did.

320
00:18:52.883 --> 00:18:53.883
With my own hands.

321
00:18:54.423 --> 00:18:56.793
I tore down the old barn.
built the greenhouse.

322
00:18:56.883 --> 00:18:57.883
<i>and the swing.</i>

323
00:18:58.673 --> 00:19:00.689
Every corner of this home...

324
00:19:00.713 --> 00:19:01.713
Honey.

325
00:19:03.423 --> 00:19:05.963
If we go bankrupt. they'll take it anyway.

326
00:19:07.213 --> 00:19:08.543
<i>The piano.</i>

327
00:19:08.633 --> 00:19:09.979
<i>living room table.</i>

328
00:19:10.003 --> 00:19:13.003
<i>two chairs. TV. curtain. carpet</i>

329
00:19:13.093 --> 00:19:14.543
have all been put up for sale.

330
00:19:14.633 --> 00:19:16.979
My racket. too.
No more tennis.

331
00:19:17.003 --> 00:19:18.729
Let's quit dance lessons. too.

332
00:19:18.753 --> 00:19:20.173
Your bonsai magazine.

333
00:19:20.793 --> 00:19:22.689
And I'm cancelling Netflix.

334
00:19:22.713 --> 00:19:24.213
[Boy sighs]

335
00:19:24.923 --> 00:19:27.019
[Music concludes;
Dog barks in the distance]

336
00:19:27.043 --> 00:19:28.899
Hey!

337
00:19:28.923 --> 00:19:31.503
Before it's cancelled.
I should watch one more show.

338
00:19:33.383 --> 00:19:35.399
[Netflix intro sound]

339
00:19:35.423 --> 00:19:39.649
So comrades. now for the bad news.

340
00:19:39.673 --> 00:19:42.229
Something even worse?

341
00:19:42.253 --> 00:19:44.343
[Dogs bark in the distance]

342
00:19:46.753 --> 00:19:50.633
In these circumstances.
we can't afford to feed so many mouths.

343
00:19:52.543 --> 00:19:54.593
What do you mean. so many?

344
00:19:55.293 --> 00:19:57.173
- Don't go. Ri-two.
- [Man-su] Ri-one.

345
00:19:58.003 --> 00:19:59.003
[Woman] Si-one.

346
00:19:59.093 --> 00:20:01.519
[Man-su] We'll see them soon. okay Ri-one?

347
00:20:01.543 --> 00:20:02.753
Come on.

348
00:20:02.843 --> 00:20:06.293
You can come visit them
at our house. Okay?

349
00:20:06.383 --> 00:20:09.439
Si-two Ri-two will be back.
As soon as Dad gets hired.

350
00:20:09.463 --> 00:20:10.519
[Dogs whimper]

351
00:20:10.543 --> 00:20:12.423
[Trunk lid beeps]

352
00:20:14.963 --> 00:20:16.519
[Ri-one breathes shakily]

353
00:20:16.543 --> 00:20:18.753
[Man sneezes]

354
00:20:21.673 --> 00:20:23.753
That dog hair is brutal.

355
00:20:23.843 --> 00:20:25.343
[Woman] I'm sorry. Dad.

356
00:20:27.543 --> 00:20:29.019
[Man-su] Have a safe drive.

357
00:20:29.043 --> 00:20:30.769
[Ri-one whimpers]

358
00:20:30.793 --> 00:20:32.593
[Woman] Let's go in. Come on.

359
00:20:34.213 --> 00:20:36.633
I'll bring them back soon. I will.

360
00:20:39.543 --> 00:20:40.713
[Horn honks]

361
00:20:43.133 --> 00:20:45.633
- Hello. ma'am!
- You're here early!

362
00:20:47.593 --> 00:20:49.963
The potential buyer is that dickhead?

363
00:20:52.633 --> 00:20:55.519
Not bad for a 50-year-old house.

364
00:20:55.543 --> 00:20:56.963
[Realtor] Look at the curtains.

365
00:20:57.593 --> 00:21:01.479
They fixed up this ruined house so well.

366
00:21:01.503 --> 00:21:03.149
It's been born again.

367
00:21:03.173 --> 00:21:06.229
- You know my townhouse near here?
- [Realtor] Yes.

368
00:21:06.253 --> 00:21:09.383
That land was originally
part of his dad's pig farm.

369
00:21:10.003 --> 00:21:12.423
Wow. if he still owned that land.

370
00:21:12.963 --> 00:21:16.253
If we tear down that greenhouse.
it'd make a great practice green.

371
00:21:19.003 --> 00:21:20.253
[He whispers] Disgusting pig.

372
00:21:20.923 --> 00:21:23.673
[Man] You're quite the handyman.
You Man-su.

373
00:21:26.003 --> 00:21:28.729
[He plays badly
the first notes of <i>Für Elise</i>]

374
00:21:28.753 --> 00:21:30.963
- That's enough for today.
- [Women converse]

375
00:21:32.003 --> 00:21:33.479
The moms are besties.

376
00:21:33.503 --> 00:21:35.213
The kids are besties.

377
00:21:37.633 --> 00:21:40.293
Oh. Pulp Man of the Year!

378
00:21:41.753 --> 00:21:43.843
Your dad's gun is still looking good.

379
00:21:44.963 --> 00:21:46.769
VIETNAM WAR SERVICE CERTIFICATE

380
00:21:46.793 --> 00:21:49.133
[Hurried footsteps approach]

381
00:21:50.543 --> 00:21:52.543
[Realtor] Oh. look here!

382
00:21:52.633 --> 00:21:58.729
Imagine waking up and seeing
that sturdy red pine!

383
00:21:58.753 --> 00:22:00.093
[Man-su] It's a white pine.

384
00:22:00.843 --> 00:22:01.979
White pine...

385
00:22:02.003 --> 00:22:04.649
Look around.
I'll stop by the dry cleaners.

386
00:22:04.673 --> 00:22:06.649
Pick up my clothes for an interview.

387
00:22:06.673 --> 00:22:08.793
[In English] You're a Man! Su! Fight!

388
00:22:11.003 --> 00:22:12.633
[In Korean] Shall we see
the kids' rooms?

389
00:22:14.593 --> 00:22:16.939
[Woman] With just one kid.
we'll use that as a closet.

390
00:22:16.963 --> 00:22:19.003
[Realtor] I thought that too!

391
00:22:20.793 --> 00:22:22.043
Nice mattress.

392
00:22:24.093 --> 00:22:26.003
That's for sale too. buy it.

393
00:22:30.463 --> 00:22:31.963
[Boy] Where will you move to?

394
00:22:33.253 --> 00:22:34.883
[Si-one] Need to sell the house first.

395
00:22:36.133 --> 00:22:37.543
[Boy] Hope you don't go far.

396
00:22:39.793 --> 00:22:42.793
If we leave. Si-two Ri-two
won't be able to find us.

397
00:22:42.883 --> 00:22:43.883
Says who?

398
00:22:53.843 --> 00:22:55.383
We're not leaving.

399
00:22:56.543 --> 00:22:57.633
I promise.

400
00:22:58.463 --> 00:23:01.753
[She repeats. rhythmically] Si-one Ri-one.
Si-one Ri-one...

401
00:23:01.843 --> 00:23:03.729
Si-two. Ri-two. Si-two...

402
00:23:03.753 --> 00:23:05.649
- [Manager] Let me through!
- [Man-su grunts]

403
00:23:05.673 --> 00:23:08.293
- I'm late for a meeting.
- [Man-su] Listen. please.

404
00:23:09.133 --> 00:23:11.753
My wife is doing part time work.

405
00:23:11.843 --> 00:23:14.293
we put our home up for sale.

406
00:23:14.383 --> 00:23:16.043
- cancelled Netflix.
- What?

407
00:23:17.463 --> 00:23:19.043
- [Man] Sir?
- Choi Sun-chul!

408
00:23:19.133 --> 00:23:21.519
[Sun-chul] What's going on? Who's this?

409
00:23:21.543 --> 00:23:23.399
He was fired from Solar.

410
00:23:23.423 --> 00:23:24.673
Just a sec.

411
00:23:27.343 --> 00:23:28.343
Come out.

412
00:23:30.003 --> 00:23:31.519
I'm sorry.

413
00:23:31.543 --> 00:23:34.003
[Sun-chul] Going to the meeting?
I wanted to talk to you.

414
00:23:34.093 --> 00:23:35.093
[Manager] Sure. then.

415
00:23:41.963 --> 00:23:44.189
Let me look.

416
00:23:44.213 --> 00:23:46.133
God. you're strong.

417
00:23:50.503 --> 00:23:52.593
If you have any shame.

418
00:23:53.253 --> 00:23:56.173
don't do this in a place
where people shit and piss.

419
00:23:59.793 --> 00:24:00.923
Sir!

420
00:24:01.593 --> 00:24:04.753
I told you to come visit me!
We'll have a nice barbecue.

421
00:24:04.843 --> 00:24:07.213
- [Manager] Alright. then.
- [He breathes shakily]

422
00:24:18.383 --> 00:24:19.633
Oh my.

423
00:24:22.253 --> 00:24:23.463
Listen.

424
00:24:24.543 --> 00:24:29.293
On the hill opposite. there's a nice
whisky bar called Moon Shine.

425
00:24:29.923 --> 00:24:31.939
- Have a drink on your way.
- [Mellow jazz music]

426
00:24:31.963 --> 00:24:35.543
<i>I just moved here to Hoi Island.</i>

427
00:24:35.633 --> 00:24:37.133
<i>It's really gorgeous.</i>

428
00:24:37.713 --> 00:24:41.543
<i>Revealed for the first time ever!
Give a shout!</i>

429
00:24:42.423 --> 00:24:46.593
<i>Barbecue over my own wood fire
is out of this world!</i>

430
00:24:47.713 --> 00:24:49.543
<i>Die!</i>

431
00:24:57.133 --> 00:24:59.383
[Music continues]

432
00:25:03.423 --> 00:25:05.979
<i>For each drop of sweat. a drop of whisky!</i>

433
00:25:06.003 --> 00:25:09.479
[In singsong] <i>It's what I live for.</i>

434
00:25:09.503 --> 00:25:12.503
- MS WIFE
- [Mobile vibrates]

435
00:25:12.593 --> 00:25:13.689
Hi honey.

436
00:25:13.713 --> 00:25:16.753
<i>Listen. the cello teacher called...</i>

437
00:25:17.463 --> 00:25:19.293
- <i>Where are you?</i>
- Huh?

438
00:25:21.293 --> 00:25:22.923
- <i>Are you in a bar?</i>
- No. no.

439
00:25:23.713 --> 00:25:25.503
Well. it's true.

440
00:25:26.463 --> 00:25:28.383
It's true. but I'm not.
Look.

441
00:25:30.383 --> 00:25:32.293
- I'm by myself.
- <i>Have you gone mad?</i>

442
00:25:33.213 --> 00:25:35.439
- I'm drinking this. really.
- [Woman] <i>Whisky?</i>

443
00:25:35.463 --> 00:25:37.189
This here.

444
00:25:37.213 --> 00:25:38.269
[She sighs]

445
00:25:38.293 --> 00:25:40.293
<i>You went to a bar
to drink apple juice?</i>

446
00:25:40.383 --> 00:25:43.293
Honey. you trust me?

447
00:25:46.133 --> 00:25:47.939
<i>Of course.</i>

448
00:25:47.963 --> 00:25:49.399
Why'd the cello teacher call?

449
00:25:49.423 --> 00:25:55.253
- I can't teach Ri-one any more.
- [Minimal cello notes]

450
00:25:56.463 --> 00:25:57.519
What?

451
00:25:57.543 --> 00:26:00.253
Ri-one's talent is too...

452
00:26:00.753 --> 00:26:01.923
outstanding?

453
00:26:07.673 --> 00:26:09.093
But ma'am.

454
00:26:10.503 --> 00:26:13.963
how can I believe you?

455
00:26:14.843 --> 00:26:18.753
She doesn't play for us.

456
00:26:19.343 --> 00:26:23.229
We've never heard anything
but a few notes.

457
00:26:23.253 --> 00:26:24.293
Right.

458
00:26:24.383 --> 00:26:30.269
Why do you think I'd give up
my lesson fee to another teacher?

459
00:26:30.293 --> 00:26:32.003
Another teacher?

460
00:26:32.093 --> 00:26:35.003
Ri-one needs to learn
from a music professor now.

461
00:26:35.093 --> 00:26:36.899
[Cello notes continue]

462
00:26:36.923 --> 00:26:40.883
But you should know.
the fee is on a different level than mine.

463
00:26:44.673 --> 00:26:50.343
You said you wanted Ri-one
to be able to live independently.

464
00:26:51.003 --> 00:26:53.003
[Notes conclude]

465
00:26:54.503 --> 00:26:56.673
If so. this level of investment...

466
00:26:57.463 --> 00:26:59.543
[Sun-chul. on video] <i>I'll say two things.</i>

467
00:27:00.753 --> 00:27:05.019
<i>Many people think paper companies
mindlessly raze entire forests. right?</i>

468
00:27:05.043 --> 00:27:07.649
- <i>That's not true. Trees for paper...</i>
- [Cello music on headphones]

469
00:27:07.673 --> 00:27:10.043
- <i>are grown separately. cut.</i>
- [Music stops]

470
00:27:10.133 --> 00:27:13.423
- <i>planted again. grown and cut again.</i>
- [Cello music resumes on headphones]

471
00:27:14.423 --> 00:27:17.019
- <i>And that's not all. There's reuse.</i>
- [Music stops]

472
00:27:17.043 --> 00:27:19.383
<i>We collect waste paper. recycle it.</i>

473
00:27:20.543 --> 00:27:23.923
- <i>then collect it again and...</i>
- [Woman] What are you watching?

474
00:27:26.963 --> 00:27:29.939
The only company doing well
these days is Moon Paper.

475
00:27:29.963 --> 00:27:33.293
They cracked the Japanese market.
He's line manager of specialty paper.

476
00:27:33.383 --> 00:27:34.479
[Cello music resumes]

477
00:27:34.503 --> 00:27:37.019
A perfect job for you.
You're good at Japanese. too.

478
00:27:37.043 --> 00:27:38.729
[Music stops]

479
00:27:38.753 --> 00:27:42.793
[Sun-chul. on video] <i>Korea's
the most advanced country in paper reuse.</i>

480
00:27:42.883 --> 00:27:44.293
[Sun-chul laughs]

481
00:27:45.003 --> 00:27:46.439
<i>Unlimited reuse!</i>

482
00:27:46.463 --> 00:27:48.293
<i>Freaking unlimited reuse!</i>

483
00:27:48.383 --> 00:27:50.383
Compared to my husband. he's nothing.

484
00:27:53.383 --> 00:27:54.979
Can't he get hit by lightning?

485
00:27:55.003 --> 00:27:56.043
[Man-su chuckles]

486
00:27:56.133 --> 00:27:58.939
Pointy umbrella in a thunderstorm.

487
00:27:58.963 --> 00:28:00.713
[They chuckle]

488
00:28:01.293 --> 00:28:03.343
[Sparse. unsettling music;
High-pitched ding]

489
00:28:04.633 --> 00:28:07.343
[Exaggerated laughter;
Melancholic. jazz-style music]

490
00:28:11.133 --> 00:28:13.729
[Indistinct chatter]

491
00:28:13.753 --> 00:28:16.213
- CHOI SUN-CHUL
- [Pouring resonates]

492
00:28:19.883 --> 00:28:22.383
[Music continues;
Pouring continues]

493
00:28:28.923 --> 00:28:31.343
[Music turns intriguing]

494
00:28:47.753 --> 00:28:49.793
[He breathes heavily]

495
00:28:51.633 --> 00:28:54.003
- Sure. it's fabulous!
- [Music concludes]

496
00:28:55.593 --> 00:28:57.843
Try living there just one week.

497
00:29:00.843 --> 00:29:03.543
An apartment can't even compare!

498
00:29:06.383 --> 00:29:07.729
[Man-su mumbles incoherently]

499
00:29:07.753 --> 00:29:10.383
Come on. the ferry runs so often!

500
00:29:13.003 --> 00:29:14.253
I'm telling you.

501
00:29:14.883 --> 00:29:18.753
I know that. but it's so quiet there.

502
00:29:19.253 --> 00:29:21.213
Air's clean. it's fabulous.

503
00:29:23.093 --> 00:29:25.673
Even more fabulous at night.

504
00:29:25.793 --> 00:29:28.213
[Birds shriek]

505
00:29:29.503 --> 00:29:31.543
[Dog grunts]

506
00:29:38.503 --> 00:29:39.503
Right.

507
00:29:42.843 --> 00:29:44.383
No. there aren't any!

508
00:29:45.503 --> 00:29:49.713
If you're scared. we'll raise chickens.
They eat snakes.

509
00:29:50.883 --> 00:29:51.883
What?

510
00:29:52.423 --> 00:29:54.423
Listen. honey.

511
00:29:55.963 --> 00:29:58.503
For once. at least come for a barbecue!

512
00:29:59.713 --> 00:30:03.173
Pork! Who roasts snakes?

513
00:30:04.593 --> 00:30:06.093
[He gasps]

514
00:30:06.673 --> 00:30:08.793
No alcohol. of course.

515
00:30:22.423 --> 00:30:24.543
[Sun-chul continues speaking below]

516
00:30:26.343 --> 00:30:28.633
[Muffled. heavy breathing]

517
00:30:30.633 --> 00:30:33.043
[Somber. unsettling music]

518
00:30:36.793 --> 00:30:39.253
[Bird's shrieking resonates]

519
00:30:42.883 --> 00:30:45.043
[He grunts. strenuously]

520
00:30:47.213 --> 00:30:48.503
[Woman] Weight lifting?

521
00:30:53.593 --> 00:30:55.093
[Sun-chul] Honey! Honey!

522
00:31:01.793 --> 00:31:04.269
[Man-su] Even if this guy disappears.

523
00:31:04.293 --> 00:31:06.253
it's not like I can take his place.

524
00:31:07.463 --> 00:31:08.463
Right?

525
00:31:09.883 --> 00:31:11.843
What's so great about that spot?

526
00:31:14.793 --> 00:31:16.963
[He moans. softly]

527
00:31:21.463 --> 00:31:23.843
The competition for the place
will be fierce.

528
00:31:25.003 --> 00:31:26.753
[Woman] Actually.
it is a pretty nice spot.

529
00:31:27.383 --> 00:31:29.383
Lots of sun. nice breeze.

530
00:31:29.963 --> 00:31:32.003
- Right...
- [Music concludes]

531
00:31:32.593 --> 00:31:35.173
How many other candidates will there be?

532
00:31:36.343 --> 00:31:37.543
Ten people?

533
00:31:41.343 --> 00:31:42.343
Five?

534
00:31:45.213 --> 00:31:47.003
MOON PAPER

535
00:31:47.093 --> 00:31:48.633
Four?

536
00:31:50.343 --> 00:31:53.093
[Faint foghorn blast in the distance]

537
00:31:55.463 --> 00:31:57.793
Sell me this.
How much do you want?

538
00:32:17.593 --> 00:32:19.213
[Line rings]

539
00:32:20.213 --> 00:32:21.729
[Call center agent] <i>This is Pulp Men.</i>

540
00:32:21.753 --> 00:32:23.883
[Man-su] Is this the advertising division?

541
00:32:24.843 --> 00:32:26.149
Hey.

542
00:32:26.173 --> 00:32:29.003
At least give me those pajamas to wash.

543
00:32:29.593 --> 00:32:31.593
And take a shower this century!

544
00:32:33.133 --> 00:32:35.439
And will you let our pear tree die?

545
00:32:35.463 --> 00:32:37.689
Bugs are swarming all over it.

546
00:32:37.713 --> 00:32:39.399
- [He passes gas]
- Hey!

547
00:32:39.423 --> 00:32:41.439
- [He giggles]
- You want me dead. too?

548
00:32:41.463 --> 00:32:43.713
[She exclaims. he laughs]

549
00:32:50.213 --> 00:32:52.293
[Cat meows]

550
00:32:56.793 --> 00:32:59.043
Too drunk to feel pain?

551
00:32:59.133 --> 00:33:01.979
You're practically paralyzed!

552
00:33:02.003 --> 00:33:05.229
[He sings] <i>♪ It's because
Of all those bugs</i>

553
00:33:05.253 --> 00:33:08.543
- <i>♪ So what I'm asking is... ♪</i>
- [Somber. drone-like music]

554
00:33:08.633 --> 00:33:11.503
[Woman 2] You're the bug!

555
00:33:11.593 --> 00:33:15.753
<i>♪ Please give me a drop of remedy ♪</i>

556
00:33:15.843 --> 00:33:17.443
[Woman 2 grunts;
Whirring and music halt]

557
00:33:17.963 --> 00:33:21.043
I'll be back late.
I have a meeting after the audition!

558
00:33:21.133 --> 00:33:22.963
[Door slams;
High-pitched beeps]

559
00:33:27.293 --> 00:33:29.423
[He breathes deeply]

560
00:33:35.003 --> 00:33:37.729
[Man-su] <i>Paper is our life!</i>

561
00:33:37.753 --> 00:33:39.753
<i>A master's degree in paper</i>

562
00:33:39.843 --> 00:33:42.939
- <i>or chemical engineering is required.</i>
- [Uplifting. plucky guitar music]

563
00:33:42.963 --> 00:33:44.753
<i>Japanese speakers preferred.</i>

564
00:33:45.253 --> 00:33:47.503
<i>We at Red Pepper Paper.</i>

565
00:33:47.593 --> 00:33:51.649
<i>together with European and Japanese firms</i>

566
00:33:51.673 --> 00:33:55.343
<i>are launching a three-company
joint venture in Korea.</i>

567
00:33:56.713 --> 00:34:02.543
<i>Our goal is to be the top boutique factory
in specialized security paper.</i>

568
00:34:03.173 --> 00:34:06.729
<i>We seek family. not cogs in a machine.</i>

569
00:34:06.753 --> 00:34:10.003
<i>Tell us about your hobbies.
personality and family.</i>

570
00:34:10.093 --> 00:34:13.229
<i>Give us a photo
as large and recent as possible.</i>

571
00:34:13.253 --> 00:34:16.769
<i>Send it to P.O. Box 76.
Gujong City Central Post Office.</i>

572
00:34:16.793 --> 00:34:19.189
<i>We firmly reject applications by internet.</i>

573
00:34:19.213 --> 00:34:21.753
<i>If we don't use paper. who will?</i>

574
00:34:25.843 --> 00:34:28.399
[Gu Bummo] <i>My name is Gu Bummo.</i>

575
00:34:28.423 --> 00:34:30.649
- <i>As a resolutely analogue person.</i>
- [Music concludes]

576
00:34:30.673 --> 00:34:32.689
<i>I play music only on vinyl.</i>

577
00:34:32.713 --> 00:34:34.769
- <i>take photos only on film.</i>
- [Upbeat soul music]

578
00:34:34.793 --> 00:34:36.633
<i>and write letters only on paper.</i>

579
00:34:38.343 --> 00:34:41.793
<i>My bond to paper.
as durable as reinforced synthetic paper.</i>

580
00:34:41.883 --> 00:34:44.463
<i>began before I was even born.</i>

581
00:34:45.593 --> 00:34:48.293
<i>Encouraged by my uncle.
a first generation paper man.</i>

582
00:34:48.383 --> 00:34:51.503
<i>I enrolled in paper manufacturing
at Kangwon University.</i>

583
00:34:53.003 --> 00:34:56.753
<i>After serving in the Marines.
I joined Namsun Paper in 1999.</i>

584
00:34:57.673 --> 00:35:01.253
<i>In 2013. I oversaw
the reinforced paper line</i>

585
00:35:01.343 --> 00:35:04.593
<i>with most of our customers
coming from the defense industry.</i>

586
00:35:05.383 --> 00:35:08.133
<i>Winning Pulp Man of the Year in 2018...</i>

587
00:35:09.503 --> 00:35:11.229
"To Red Pepper Paper HR."

588
00:35:11.253 --> 00:35:13.173
[Gu Bummo] <i>...was the pinnacle
of my career.</i>

589
00:35:13.713 --> 00:35:16.753
<i>but in 2023 the Defense Ministry
had a change in strategy</i>

590
00:35:16.843 --> 00:35:19.439
- <i>causing our production line to close.</i>
- [Ri-one reads letter]

591
00:35:19.463 --> 00:35:23.189
[Gu Bummo] <i>Namsun Paper
merged with Mori Paper.</i>

592
00:35:23.213 --> 00:35:26.753
<i>and all specialty paper personnel
such as myself</i>

593
00:35:26.843 --> 00:35:28.923
<i>had to leave the company.</i>

594
00:35:29.963 --> 00:35:34.439
<i>I've now been eight months between jobs.</i>

595
00:35:34.463 --> 00:35:37.253
<i>and I feel my batteries
are completely charged.</i>

596
00:35:38.253 --> 00:35:39.793
<i>During my extensive free time.</i>

597
00:35:39.883 --> 00:35:41.253
<i>I...</i>

598
00:35:41.343 --> 00:35:43.673
[Music intensifies]

599
00:36:24.343 --> 00:36:25.793
PULP MAN OF THE YEAR

600
00:36:25.883 --> 00:36:27.043
FIRE SAFETY CERTIFICATION

601
00:36:49.673 --> 00:36:52.003
- WORKED TWO YEARS AT ISHII PAPER IN JAPAN
- [Man-su sighs]

602
00:36:53.003 --> 00:36:55.003
[Music dies down]

603
00:37:25.503 --> 00:37:27.293
- NORTH KOREA TYPE 64 PISTOL
- [Man-su] One.

604
00:37:29.543 --> 00:37:30.633
two.

605
00:37:32.793 --> 00:37:33.963
three men...

606
00:37:36.753 --> 00:37:38.899
[He exhales deeply]

607
00:37:38.923 --> 00:37:41.003
[Birds chirp]

608
00:37:47.253 --> 00:37:48.753
[Soft. strained moan]

609
00:37:51.093 --> 00:37:53.423
[Soft squelching and crackling]

610
00:38:21.753 --> 00:38:22.753
[Car alarm beeps]

611
00:38:31.543 --> 00:38:33.503
[Strained breathing]

612
00:38:46.133 --> 00:38:47.213
[He sighs. bitterly]

613
00:38:50.843 --> 00:38:52.093
Huh?

614
00:39:15.673 --> 00:39:17.633
[He grunts]

615
00:39:23.713 --> 00:39:25.883
[Elegant. contemplative string music]

616
00:39:27.173 --> 00:39:29.189
[Music continues on speaker]

617
00:39:29.213 --> 00:39:30.753
How was your day?

618
00:39:35.423 --> 00:39:36.673
Daddy's day was hard.

619
00:39:38.343 --> 00:39:41.173
There's this house
with a beautiful pear tree.

620
00:39:42.253 --> 00:39:45.673
- but bugs are eating it alive.
- [Music comes and goes as swing moves]

621
00:39:46.463 --> 00:39:47.843
It made me sad.

622
00:39:53.633 --> 00:39:58.543
In these circumstances.
we can't afford to feed so many mouths.

623
00:40:01.043 --> 00:40:03.213
[Music swells]

624
00:40:15.093 --> 00:40:16.189
[Resolute final note]

625
00:40:16.213 --> 00:40:17.793
Oh. fuck!

626
00:40:18.503 --> 00:40:20.633
[Birds chirp]

627
00:40:45.503 --> 00:40:48.229
- [Woman 2] Eating any old mushroom again!
- [Man-su gasps]

628
00:40:48.253 --> 00:40:50.383
You quit drinking.
and now you'll eat anything?

629
00:40:53.133 --> 00:40:55.093
My back will ache without a blanket.

630
00:40:57.543 --> 00:40:58.793
Why would you lie down?

631
00:41:00.093 --> 00:41:01.649
Not scared of a snake?

632
00:41:01.673 --> 00:41:03.883
[She huffs. he reacts surprised]

633
00:41:10.673 --> 00:41:13.269
They haven't called for an interview.

634
00:41:13.293 --> 00:41:14.543
They'll call.

635
00:41:15.133 --> 00:41:16.399
Do like me.

636
00:41:16.423 --> 00:41:17.689
[She swallows air]

637
00:41:17.713 --> 00:41:18.753
What?

638
00:41:18.843 --> 00:41:22.479
Wrap the sunlight in wind
and take a bite.

639
00:41:22.503 --> 00:41:25.213
With a dollop of foliage.

640
00:41:27.383 --> 00:41:30.343
I've always at least gotten an interview.

641
00:41:32.923 --> 00:41:34.003
[Woman 2] What about me?

642
00:41:34.543 --> 00:41:36.729
[Man-su breathes nervously]

643
00:41:36.753 --> 00:41:38.963
I failed my audition again!

644
00:41:40.713 --> 00:41:43.043
My skin's too firm

645
00:41:43.133 --> 00:41:45.843
to play a woman wailing
over her husband's death.

646
00:41:49.093 --> 00:41:52.543
Still. it was nice being
at the Arts Center after so long.

647
00:41:56.923 --> 00:41:59.019
Remember the night of the blackout?

648
00:41:59.043 --> 00:42:00.423
Our first play seen together.

649
00:42:01.133 --> 00:42:02.979
In Act Two. suddenly the lights go out.

650
00:42:03.003 --> 00:42:06.593
People panic. women scream.

651
00:42:07.963 --> 00:42:10.003
and I was about to have a panic attack.

652
00:42:10.093 --> 00:42:11.503
when you appeared.

653
00:42:11.593 --> 00:42:13.003
Suddenly. from who knows where.

654
00:42:13.093 --> 00:42:15.543
- like a street light turning on.
- [Tender Korean ballad]

655
00:42:15.633 --> 00:42:16.689
your face...

656
00:42:16.713 --> 00:42:18.713
[Delicate. warm explosion]

657
00:42:19.093 --> 00:42:24.269
[Soft female voice sings] <i>♪ Please
light a flame ♪</i>

658
00:42:24.293 --> 00:42:26.649
[Panicked screaming in background]

659
00:42:26.673 --> 00:42:30.793
<i>♪ In my lonely heart... ♪</i>

660
00:42:30.883 --> 00:42:32.093
[Woman 2] <i>Smiling.</i>

661
00:42:32.793 --> 00:42:34.253
<i>you lead me to the door.</i>

662
00:42:34.343 --> 00:42:37.843
[Woman 2] <i>"Ara. follow me. Only me."</i>

663
00:42:39.713 --> 00:42:40.843
<i>"Watch your step."</i>

664
00:42:43.843 --> 00:42:44.923
<i>"Are you okay?"</i>

665
00:42:45.963 --> 00:42:48.793
- I was at my most innocent then.
- [Music dies down]

666
00:42:50.713 --> 00:42:52.293
Plump and pretty.

667
00:42:53.343 --> 00:42:55.543
<i>I let you have my first kiss.</i>

668
00:42:56.423 --> 00:42:58.293
[Loud crunching]

669
00:43:01.963 --> 00:43:03.463
Remember what you said?

670
00:43:04.503 --> 00:43:06.633
[Ballad resumes]

671
00:43:07.383 --> 00:43:11.423
<i>"Ara. your lips are softer than
the highest quality Okamoto</i>

672
00:43:12.633 --> 00:43:13.673
<i>"tracing paper."</i>

673
00:43:14.673 --> 00:43:16.253
- [Gu Bummo] Akimoto.
- [Man-su mouths]

674
00:43:16.343 --> 00:43:18.133
Okamoto is a condom brand.

675
00:43:19.213 --> 00:43:20.979
"Ara. your lips

676
00:43:21.003 --> 00:43:24.479
<i>"are softer than the highest quality
Akimoto tracing paper."</i>

677
00:43:24.503 --> 00:43:25.503
[Ara laughs]

678
00:43:30.343 --> 00:43:32.383
[Loud crunching;
Music dies down]

679
00:43:33.753 --> 00:43:36.503
[Gu Bummo] No message. no email.

680
00:43:36.593 --> 00:43:38.503
Paper. paper! Damned paper!

681
00:43:39.293 --> 00:43:41.793
My dad kept offering
to set you up with a café.

682
00:43:41.883 --> 00:43:43.673
but no. it had to be paper!

683
00:43:44.213 --> 00:43:48.293
Even if they hire you. you'll retire
in six. seven years. What then?

684
00:43:48.883 --> 00:43:50.769
In an age of living to 100?

685
00:43:50.793 --> 00:43:52.753
You with your nice audio system.

686
00:43:52.843 --> 00:43:54.843
you could earn even more
with a music café!

687
00:43:55.463 --> 00:43:56.883
Know how I feel lately?

688
00:43:57.793 --> 00:43:59.293
I want to run through the mountains.

689
00:43:59.383 --> 00:44:01.689
[Her voice subsides] wailing
like a madwoman!

690
00:44:01.713 --> 00:44:02.963
[She screams]

691
00:44:03.093 --> 00:44:06.399
I'm like one of your precious
paper machines.

692
00:44:06.423 --> 00:44:08.399
Neglect me. and I'll break!

693
00:44:08.423 --> 00:44:11.673
Hurry up and smother me in that lube oil!

694
00:44:12.343 --> 00:44:16.133
Or I'll rip you to pieces.
Like tracing paper!

695
00:44:17.633 --> 00:44:19.753
Paper has fed me for 25 years.

696
00:44:20.923 --> 00:44:22.253
Honey.

697
00:44:22.843 --> 00:44:25.293
It's how I'm meant to be.
I've no other choice.

698
00:44:25.383 --> 00:44:28.463
You've been fed by the money
I earned from paper. too.

699
00:44:29.593 --> 00:44:31.463
That money was printed on paper I made.

700
00:44:32.043 --> 00:44:34.633
and the cigarette filter
you smoke is paper. too.

701
00:44:36.503 --> 00:44:38.293
If we don't use paper. who will?

702
00:44:38.383 --> 00:44:39.923
What?

703
00:44:41.593 --> 00:44:43.423
They won't send a text or email.

704
00:44:44.093 --> 00:44:45.689
The mailbox! The mailbox!

705
00:44:45.713 --> 00:44:47.343
Hey! Hey!

706
00:44:49.043 --> 00:44:51.399
I'm through with you!

707
00:44:51.423 --> 00:44:52.633
You...

708
00:44:53.173 --> 00:44:56.003
As useless as scrap paper!

709
00:44:56.093 --> 00:44:57.093
[He groans]

710
00:44:57.923 --> 00:44:59.463
Sorry to keep you waiting.

711
00:45:00.963 --> 00:45:05.293
- I'll check before the doctor comes.
- Yes.

712
00:45:07.423 --> 00:45:08.593
You're a nurse?

713
00:45:09.383 --> 00:45:12.133
Dental hygienist. It's different.

714
00:45:14.543 --> 00:45:16.689
Don't you have dance class now?

715
00:45:16.713 --> 00:45:18.713
My tooth hurts too much.

716
00:45:20.253 --> 00:45:22.093
Then say "ah".

717
00:45:24.963 --> 00:45:27.293
You'll come to the dance party. though?

718
00:45:28.043 --> 00:45:30.479
How can I? I quit the lessons.

719
00:45:30.503 --> 00:45:33.689
You can still come! Ask the teacher.

720
00:45:33.713 --> 00:45:35.769
Ms Lee. go on home.

721
00:45:35.793 --> 00:45:37.269
You need to pick up Ri-one.

722
00:45:37.293 --> 00:45:38.503
[Woman] Yes.

723
00:45:39.253 --> 00:45:43.439
You were a thing pure.
noble. honest. without stain!

724
00:45:43.463 --> 00:45:45.293
- And now... oh!
- [Leaves rustle]

725
00:45:45.383 --> 00:45:48.793
When I think that I made
of a man like you my ideal!

726
00:45:48.883 --> 00:45:51.729
Dear me! The ideal of my life!

727
00:45:51.753 --> 00:45:53.883
[Weak groans]

728
00:45:54.883 --> 00:45:56.293
[Man-su] Fucking snake!

729
00:45:57.593 --> 00:45:59.503
[He grunts. she gasps]

730
00:46:00.133 --> 00:46:01.593
Was its head triangle-shaped?

731
00:46:02.713 --> 00:46:05.343
Then it's a cannibal viper.
It'll eat its own mother.

732
00:46:06.503 --> 00:46:08.729
Or was it a black-and-white pattern?

733
00:46:08.753 --> 00:46:12.019
Then it's a seven-step mamushi.
You'll die before taking seven steps.

734
00:46:12.043 --> 00:46:14.043
I think I heard a rattle. too.

735
00:46:15.343 --> 00:46:18.043
Keep the bite wound
higher than your heart.

736
00:46:22.093 --> 00:46:23.423
Shouldn't it be lower?

737
00:46:24.633 --> 00:46:28.399
Don't worry. I did this in a play once.

738
00:46:28.423 --> 00:46:29.423
Did what?

739
00:46:30.593 --> 00:46:32.043
[He grunts]

740
00:46:52.543 --> 00:46:54.649
[Mobile vibrates]

741
00:46:54.673 --> 00:46:56.593
[She spits]

742
00:46:56.713 --> 00:46:58.793
- <i>Honey. know what?</i>
- Listen...

743
00:46:58.883 --> 00:47:00.269
A snake just bit me.

744
00:47:00.293 --> 00:47:02.423
- <i>What?</i>
- Might be poisonous. I'll call you back.

745
00:47:05.883 --> 00:47:08.093
[Loud. wet sucking]

746
00:47:17.843 --> 00:47:20.633
Chase the snakes away like this.

747
00:47:21.633 --> 00:47:23.019
Damn it!

748
00:47:23.043 --> 00:47:26.343
1. KEEP BITE LOWER THAN HEART.
2. DON'T CUT. OR SUCK OUT POISON.

749
00:47:28.343 --> 00:47:29.399
For god's sake!

750
00:47:29.423 --> 00:47:30.479
[He clicks his tongue]

751
00:47:30.503 --> 00:47:32.399
[Woman] Shouldn't you go to the hospital?

752
00:47:32.423 --> 00:47:34.293
It's okay.

753
00:47:34.383 --> 00:47:36.753
If it were poisonous. I'd be dead now.

754
00:47:41.213 --> 00:47:44.633
- [Music plays - <i>Loie</i>. by Ike Quebec]
- [He chuckles provocatively]

755
00:47:47.173 --> 00:47:48.253
What's with you?

756
00:47:51.843 --> 00:47:54.189
About the dance party.

757
00:47:54.213 --> 00:47:58.269
We better not go. right?
We quit the lessons.

758
00:47:58.293 --> 00:48:01.093
What? But we practiced so much.

759
00:48:04.753 --> 00:48:06.979
It's from the first mixtape you gave me.

760
00:48:07.003 --> 00:48:10.343
[She huffs] For a guy
who only listens to '80s rock.

761
00:48:10.843 --> 00:48:12.633
I was blinded by love.

762
00:48:13.293 --> 00:48:16.149
I think I was prettiest back then.

763
00:48:16.173 --> 00:48:18.519
Even if I was a divorcee with a kid.

764
00:48:18.543 --> 00:48:20.939
Hey. don't talk like that.

765
00:48:20.963 --> 00:48:23.673
Of course. I earned more money than you.

766
00:48:24.883 --> 00:48:26.149
What?

767
00:48:26.173 --> 00:48:29.189
You think I proposed
because of your pay check?

768
00:48:29.213 --> 00:48:31.713
Who knows? I had a college degree too.

769
00:48:33.093 --> 00:48:35.133
- So did I.
- Not back then.

770
00:48:37.423 --> 00:48:39.423
You're so mean. Forget it.

771
00:48:40.003 --> 00:48:43.543
You were busy doing
the distance degree while working.

772
00:48:43.633 --> 00:48:45.979
I wanted so much
to have fun with you then.

773
00:48:46.003 --> 00:48:49.253
Apologise. will you? Right now.

774
00:48:49.343 --> 00:48:50.899
[Man-su. chuckling] You're right.

775
00:48:50.923 --> 00:48:55.923
Let's have ten times more fun now
instead of wasting time complaining.

776
00:48:57.133 --> 00:48:59.043
When should we tell Si-one?

777
00:49:00.043 --> 00:49:01.293
Tell him what?

778
00:49:01.883 --> 00:49:04.963
We agreed to tell him
when he's old enough to shave.

779
00:49:06.343 --> 00:49:08.383
But do we have to tell him?

780
00:49:09.383 --> 00:49:11.793
I've been his dad since he was two.
so I'm his dad.

781
00:49:17.543 --> 00:49:18.923
I'm sorry. Miri.

782
00:49:19.883 --> 00:49:23.543
You must want some lube oil too.
I've been so...

783
00:49:24.843 --> 00:49:26.383
Lube oil?

784
00:49:28.003 --> 00:49:29.293
It's not that.

785
00:49:30.423 --> 00:49:34.213
I've just been so busy these days
with job interviews.

786
00:49:34.923 --> 00:49:36.883
Does it have to be paper?

787
00:49:37.383 --> 00:49:39.043
How about some other job?

788
00:49:40.343 --> 00:49:41.423
What?

789
00:49:42.093 --> 00:49:43.173
Like a café?

790
00:49:44.383 --> 00:49:45.753
Why a café?

791
00:49:46.883 --> 00:49:49.593
Paper has fed me for 25 years. honey.

792
00:49:50.383 --> 00:49:52.423
It's how I'm meant to be.

793
00:49:53.343 --> 00:49:54.729
Think about it.

794
00:49:54.753 --> 00:49:58.649
would you tell a cannibal viper
to live off pear leaves?

795
00:49:58.673 --> 00:50:01.503
It's meant to eat its mother.

796
00:50:01.593 --> 00:50:03.713
[Music continues]

797
00:50:04.713 --> 00:50:08.043
- Is that so. Mr You?
- Yes.

798
00:50:08.133 --> 00:50:10.229
- Mr You.
- [Man-su] Yes?

799
00:50:10.253 --> 00:50:11.593
You're not a bad dancer.

800
00:50:12.503 --> 00:50:13.979
Follow me. Only me.

801
00:50:14.003 --> 00:50:15.189
[Music dies down]

802
00:50:15.213 --> 00:50:17.729
Guess you overdid the vibrato.

803
00:50:17.753 --> 00:50:20.753
- [Ri-one moans. softly]
- [Miri hums. happily]

804
00:50:33.923 --> 00:50:36.503
This will be the best job interview ever.

805
00:50:36.593 --> 00:50:38.003
Slay them all!

806
00:50:38.633 --> 00:50:41.149
Okay. I'll slay them all.

807
00:50:41.173 --> 00:50:42.423
Green light!

808
00:50:44.043 --> 00:50:46.003
[Car alarm beeps]

809
00:50:51.883 --> 00:50:53.883
[Man-su pants]

810
00:50:58.293 --> 00:51:00.963
[Elegant. unsettling string music]

811
00:51:10.713 --> 00:51:13.003
[Moaning and groaning]

812
00:51:15.713 --> 00:51:16.883
[Ara] Chun-oh!

813
00:51:17.753 --> 00:51:18.899
Chun-oh!

814
00:51:18.923 --> 00:51:21.003
[Ara moans]

815
00:51:21.093 --> 00:51:23.043
[Music continues]

816
00:51:23.633 --> 00:51:25.229
[Chun-oh grunts]

817
00:51:25.253 --> 00:51:30.003
[Chun-oh] Doing it on your bed
is great. ma'am. It doesn't even creak.

818
00:51:30.093 --> 00:51:32.689
[Ara] Don't call me ma'am!

819
00:51:32.713 --> 00:51:35.883
[Chun-oh] Tell your husband not to quit

820
00:51:36.843 --> 00:51:39.753
that group for quitting drinking.
This is great.

821
00:51:43.383 --> 00:51:45.503
[Music halts. resonates]

822
00:51:53.383 --> 00:51:54.543
Oh!

823
00:51:55.753 --> 00:51:58.043
[Tires screech]

824
00:51:58.133 --> 00:52:00.673
[Tense. anticipatory string music]

825
00:52:09.923 --> 00:52:12.093
[Man-su gasps]

826
00:52:18.543 --> 00:52:20.043
MINSAN CITY...

827
00:52:21.793 --> 00:52:24.293
[Music continues]

828
00:52:27.093 --> 00:52:29.293
[Line rings]

829
00:52:40.043 --> 00:52:43.229
- Hello. this is Red Pepper Paper.
- [Music thins. suspends]

830
00:52:43.253 --> 00:52:44.769
<i>Oh. hello!</i>

831
00:52:44.793 --> 00:52:47.043
- Hey. don't!
- [Gu Bummo] <i>What?</i>

832
00:52:47.133 --> 00:52:49.173
Yes? Hello? What was that?

833
00:52:49.793 --> 00:52:51.043
I'm having trouble hearing you.

834
00:52:52.093 --> 00:52:53.479
<i>I can hear you fine.</i>

835
00:52:53.503 --> 00:52:55.793
I heard well from the spot
where you first answered.

836
00:52:56.843 --> 00:53:00.229
<i>I see! I'm heading there now.</i>

837
00:53:00.253 --> 00:53:01.399
[Man-su] Stop!

838
00:53:01.423 --> 00:53:02.673
That spot is perfect.

839
00:53:03.883 --> 00:53:05.519
You can hear best from here?

840
00:53:05.543 --> 00:53:07.503
[Man-su] <i>Yes. I can hear you great now.</i>

841
00:53:08.293 --> 00:53:11.503
By any chance are you
at your home in Minsan City?

842
00:53:12.253 --> 00:53:13.253
I am.

843
00:53:13.343 --> 00:53:15.503
My boss would like to meet you.

844
00:53:16.293 --> 00:53:18.923
<i>He's very curious about you. Mr Gu.</i>

845
00:53:19.593 --> 00:53:20.939
- However...
- <i>Yes?</i>

846
00:53:20.963 --> 00:53:25.753
My boss is returning to Zurich
on a 5pm flight.

847
00:53:26.793 --> 00:53:31.923
I'm sorry. but if you leave from Minsan
right now. you should have time.

848
00:53:33.503 --> 00:53:34.729
<i>Right now?</i>

849
00:53:34.753 --> 00:53:36.793
Guess it's too much to ask?

850
00:53:37.843 --> 00:53:41.649
Okay. then I'll tell him you're not...

851
00:53:41.673 --> 00:53:42.963
No. no!

852
00:53:43.503 --> 00:53:44.793
I can go.

853
00:53:44.883 --> 00:53:47.543
Of course! I'll go.

854
00:53:47.633 --> 00:53:49.293
[Man-su] <i>Then I'll text you right now</i>

855
00:53:49.383 --> 00:53:53.003
with the address of our office.
so please set off now.

856
00:53:53.093 --> 00:53:54.593
<i>Of course. yes.</i>

857
00:53:55.173 --> 00:53:57.173
- [He hesitates] Huh...
- [Music concludes]

858
00:53:58.253 --> 00:54:01.503
I'll just change clothes quickly and go.

859
00:54:01.593 --> 00:54:03.189
<i>Text me the address!</i>

860
00:54:03.213 --> 00:54:05.019
No. no! You're fine as you...

861
00:54:05.043 --> 00:54:06.753
[Man-su exclaims. bitterly]

862
00:54:08.883 --> 00:54:11.173
[Wind rustles]

863
00:54:29.043 --> 00:54:31.343
[Bummo sobs. quietly]

864
00:54:47.293 --> 00:54:49.173
[He sighs. wearily]

865
00:54:53.633 --> 00:54:55.673
[He breathes heavily]

866
00:55:05.383 --> 00:55:06.543
[His voice breaks] Bitch.

867
00:55:06.633 --> 00:55:09.343
NO NEW MESSAGES

868
00:55:15.843 --> 00:55:18.133
- [Mobile vibrates]
- [He startles]

869
00:55:20.713 --> 00:55:21.753
Please answer.

870
00:55:22.423 --> 00:55:24.793
[Line rings;
Vibrating continues]

871
00:55:30.633 --> 00:55:31.793
Come on. pick up.

872
00:55:32.463 --> 00:55:34.003
[Voicemail answers]

873
00:55:34.923 --> 00:55:37.003
[Insect buzzes]

874
00:55:52.673 --> 00:55:55.753
Hey. how are you? Busy?

875
00:55:56.463 --> 00:55:57.673
Bad reception?

876
00:55:58.503 --> 00:56:00.793
No way! The signal's best here.

877
00:56:01.923 --> 00:56:03.093
You hear me. right?

878
00:56:03.633 --> 00:56:08.519
Well. I went to some gathering
without seeing that it got cancelled.

879
00:56:08.543 --> 00:56:11.503
So I came back early.
and now I'm feeling so bored.

880
00:56:12.753 --> 00:56:14.043
My wife?

881
00:56:15.253 --> 00:56:16.343
Not sure.

882
00:56:18.463 --> 00:56:19.793
Maybe she went out.

883
00:56:22.423 --> 00:56:24.253
Want to catch up over a drink?

884
00:56:25.843 --> 00:56:30.963
I quit. sure. but now it's under control.
I can drink reasonably.

885
00:56:32.133 --> 00:56:33.399
[He chuckles]

886
00:56:33.423 --> 00:56:34.423
Exactly!

887
00:56:35.503 --> 00:56:37.593
See you at the fried chicken place.

888
00:56:38.593 --> 00:56:41.963
Come when you finish work.
I'll wait there.

889
00:56:42.883 --> 00:56:45.593
[Wind blows;
Somber. unsettling string music]

890
00:56:55.843 --> 00:56:58.093
OH CHIN-HO'S DENTAL CLINIC

891
00:57:01.093 --> 00:57:02.543
- Hello.
- Yeah.

892
00:57:08.503 --> 00:57:10.463
- Hi Ri-one.
- [Miri] You're late.

893
00:57:21.003 --> 00:57:22.793
I'll throw it out.

894
00:57:22.883 --> 00:57:23.883
Thank you.

895
00:57:28.753 --> 00:57:31.253
I waited to say hello to you.
I'm Oh Chin-ho.

896
00:57:32.343 --> 00:57:34.769
- You've got a bad toothache?
- Yeah.

897
00:57:34.793 --> 00:57:35.963
Stop by some time.

898
00:57:37.003 --> 00:57:39.439
- Could you lower the window?
- I'm okay.

899
00:57:39.463 --> 00:57:41.463
I'm totally fine. Mr Oh Chun-oh.

900
00:57:43.293 --> 00:57:46.173
Thank you. Doctor Oh. Chin. Ho.

901
00:57:46.713 --> 00:57:48.593
Thanks! Go home now.

902
00:57:49.593 --> 00:57:51.923
[Car revs]

903
00:57:53.713 --> 00:57:56.133
- [She mimics revving]
- Goddamned embarrassing.

904
00:58:02.633 --> 00:58:05.253
Ri-one. it's okay now.

905
00:58:05.343 --> 00:58:08.253
Dad's not a very
smooth driver. that's all.

906
00:58:09.213 --> 00:58:11.963
He's young. Quite an age gap.

907
00:58:12.843 --> 00:58:13.899
Age gap?

908
00:58:13.923 --> 00:58:15.253
[She scoffs]

909
00:58:15.343 --> 00:58:16.399
With who?

910
00:58:16.423 --> 00:58:18.883
I'd rather you not
talk to that man about me.

911
00:58:20.293 --> 00:58:22.503
[Warm. nostalgic Korean ballad]

912
00:58:29.963 --> 00:58:32.503
[He moans. softly]

913
00:58:40.293 --> 00:58:42.883
[Music intensifies]

914
00:58:46.463 --> 00:58:48.753
- <i>♪ It may be ♪</i>
- [Music rhythm accelerates]

915
00:58:48.843 --> 00:58:51.769
<i>♪ That I'm still just a child ♪</i>

916
00:58:51.793 --> 00:58:53.149
[Music subsides]

917
00:58:53.173 --> 00:58:55.689
- <i>♪ It seems so ♪</i>
- [She gasps]

918
00:58:55.713 --> 00:58:59.003
- [Music grows louder]
- <i>♪ Mom. why do I</i>

919
00:58:59.093 --> 00:59:01.269
<i>♪ Keep waiting for you? ♪</i>

920
00:59:01.293 --> 00:59:03.649
[Music subsides]

921
00:59:03.673 --> 00:59:06.963
<i>♪ Mom. why do I ♪</i>

922
00:59:07.673 --> 00:59:11.543
- [Music grows louder]
- <i>♪ Suddenly miss you so?</i>

923
00:59:12.133 --> 00:59:13.899
<i>♪ It may be</i>

924
00:59:13.923 --> 00:59:17.383
<i>♪ That I'm still just a child</i>

925
00:59:18.383 --> 00:59:20.519
<i>♪ It seems so</i>

926
00:59:20.543 --> 00:59:24.043
<i>♪ Mom. why do I</i>

927
00:59:24.713 --> 00:59:28.383
- <i>♪ Keep feeling sad? ♪</i>
- [Music obscures dialogue]

928
00:59:28.923 --> 00:59:32.343
<i>♪ Mom. why do I... ♪</i>

929
00:59:32.463 --> 00:59:34.883
{\an8}[He yells] The two of us can't live
under the same sky.

930
00:59:37.383 --> 00:59:39.883
{\an8}[Music rhythm slows down]

931
00:59:40.003 --> 00:59:43.149
{\an8}[Shouting over blaring music] Want
to end this with a duel?

932
00:59:43.173 --> 00:59:44.883
{\an8}Does Ara know you're doing this.

933
00:59:45.383 --> 00:59:46.883
{\an8}newcomer actor Lee Chun-oh?

934
00:59:47.213 --> 00:59:48.213
{\an8}Who?

935
00:59:48.463 --> 00:59:49.713
{\an8}Were you baking.

936
00:59:49.963 --> 00:59:50.963
{\an8}and suddenly.

937
00:59:51.633 --> 00:59:53.713
{\an8}decided you want Ara all to yourself?

938
00:59:56.253 --> 00:59:57.843
{\an8}[Barely audible] Exactly!

939
01:00:05.423 --> 01:00:08.899
<i>♪ With my heart steeped in loneliness</i>

940
01:00:08.923 --> 01:00:12.293
<i>♪ I gaze up at the sky</i>

941
01:00:12.383 --> 01:00:16.503
<i>♪ And the clouds flow past ♪</i>

942
01:00:17.503 --> 01:00:19.293
- [Music subsides]
- <i>♪ Making me dizzy</i>

943
01:00:19.383 --> 01:00:22.769
<i>♪ Making my head spin</i>

944
01:00:22.793 --> 01:00:25.793
<i>♪ As the red dragonfly flies off... ♪</i>

945
01:00:25.883 --> 01:00:28.093
{\an8}- [Music grows louder]
- Sorry.

946
01:00:28.753 --> 01:00:29.963
{\an8}But you must disappear...

947
01:00:31.003 --> 01:00:32.149
{\an8}for me to live.

948
01:00:32.173 --> 01:00:34.383
{\an8}[Music rhythm accelerates]

949
01:00:40.753 --> 01:00:43.253
{\an8}[Music blasts louder]

950
01:00:46.923 --> 01:00:47.979
{\an8}Know your place!

951
01:00:48.003 --> 01:00:50.093
{\an8}The man Ara loves is me!

952
01:00:56.293 --> 01:00:58.043
{\an8}- [He shouts] You sure?
- [He shouts] What!

953
01:00:58.593 --> 01:01:00.133
{\an8}Can't an unemployed man love?

954
01:01:00.673 --> 01:01:01.673
{\an8}That's not it!

955
01:01:02.503 --> 01:01:03.923
{\an8}That's not it at all. but...

956
01:01:04.883 --> 01:01:05.883
{\an8}You...

957
01:01:08.003 --> 01:01:09.003
{\an8}did not...

958
01:01:09.293 --> 01:01:11.213
{\an8}even listen to

959
01:01:11.633 --> 01:01:13.293
{\an8}your wife's sensible suggestions!

960
01:01:13.753 --> 01:01:14.753
{\an8}Damn. my throat.

961
01:01:16.003 --> 01:01:17.593
{\an8}What's wrong with a music café?

962
01:01:23.213 --> 01:01:26.213
{\an8}- She even told you that?
- [Music rhythm slows down]

963
01:01:28.963 --> 01:01:30.843
{\an8}If you can't earn money. sell the house!

964
01:01:32.343 --> 01:01:34.133
{\an8}Work at a retail store moving boxes!

965
01:01:35.093 --> 01:01:36.883
{\an8}I'm an engineer!

966
01:01:37.593 --> 01:01:38.593
{\an8}An expert!

967
01:01:41.213 --> 01:01:42.213
{\an8}The house...

968
01:01:42.963 --> 01:01:44.963
{\an8}is Ara's father's. so I can't sell it.

969
01:01:46.213 --> 01:01:47.213
{\an8}The boxes...

970
01:01:48.793 --> 01:01:50.673
{\an8}hurt my back. so I can't lift them!

971
01:01:51.503 --> 01:01:52.503
{\an8}You proud of that?

972
01:01:52.593 --> 01:01:53.793
{\an8}[Startled breath]

973
01:01:57.293 --> 01:01:59.593
{\an8}[He howls in pain]

974
01:02:00.793 --> 01:02:02.343
{\an8}If you found out. tell me!

975
01:02:02.543 --> 01:02:03.843
{\an8}Why not say something?

976
01:02:06.293 --> 01:02:08.383
{\an8}[She screams]

977
01:02:17.673 --> 01:02:20.343
{\an8}- [Music rhythm accelerates]
- [They scream and grunt]

978
01:02:22.793 --> 01:02:23.963
{\an8}[Gu Bummo] And if I do?

979
01:02:24.793 --> 01:02:27.269
{\an8}- Will you come back?
- [Ara] Huh?

980
01:02:27.293 --> 01:02:29.003
{\an8}Snake bite! You fucker!

981
01:02:31.923 --> 01:02:34.133
{\an8}[He howls in pain]

982
01:02:36.043 --> 01:02:37.293
{\an8}Honey! Honey!

983
01:02:59.883 --> 01:03:01.673
[Music dies down]

984
01:03:02.173 --> 01:03:04.479
[Grunting continues]

985
01:03:04.503 --> 01:03:05.843
You shithead!

986
01:03:06.423 --> 01:03:08.423
[Record whirs]

987
01:03:13.093 --> 01:03:14.883
[Gunshot]

988
01:03:16.173 --> 01:03:18.173
[They breath sharply]

989
01:03:28.543 --> 01:03:29.673
[Gu Bummo] The gun!

990
01:03:30.173 --> 01:03:31.503
Give me the gun!

991
01:03:31.963 --> 01:03:33.253
I'm an ex-Marine!

992
01:03:33.343 --> 01:03:35.383
[He pants]

993
01:03:41.673 --> 01:03:43.753
[Gu Bummo grunts. furiously]

994
01:03:48.003 --> 01:03:49.793
[Gunshot]

995
01:03:50.133 --> 01:03:52.383
[He pants]

996
01:03:55.043 --> 01:03:56.713
[Insect buzzes]

997
01:03:58.423 --> 01:03:59.463
Losing my job

998
01:04:00.543 --> 01:04:02.729
is not my choice.

999
01:04:02.753 --> 01:04:04.293
How many times must I say it?

1000
01:04:05.633 --> 01:04:08.753
Losing your job isn't the problem!

1001
01:04:08.843 --> 01:04:14.173
The problem is how you deal with it!

1002
01:04:17.843 --> 01:04:19.293
[He breathes shakily]

1003
01:04:20.093 --> 01:04:21.503
Oh. come on.

1004
01:04:24.043 --> 01:04:25.923
You going to die from two bullets?

1005
01:04:29.343 --> 01:04:32.753
[Startled. whimpering gasps;
Elegant. melancholic classical music]

1006
01:04:34.253 --> 01:04:36.133
[She screams]

1007
01:04:38.923 --> 01:04:40.923
[Gunshot]

1008
01:04:45.293 --> 01:04:47.383
[He screams in panic]

1009
01:05:04.173 --> 01:05:06.173
[They scream]

1010
01:05:17.253 --> 01:05:19.503
[Shuddered breathing]

1011
01:05:21.423 --> 01:05:23.149
[He whimpers]

1012
01:05:23.173 --> 01:05:25.173
MS WIFE - TEN MISSED CALLS

1013
01:05:30.133 --> 01:05:31.189
Fucking...

1014
01:05:31.213 --> 01:05:33.043
hell!

1015
01:05:33.133 --> 01:05:35.543
[Screaming concludes. resonates;
Music halts]

1016
01:05:36.383 --> 01:05:38.673
[Insects chirp]

1017
01:05:41.043 --> 01:05:42.793
[Boy] These ones sell for a lot.

1018
01:05:42.883 --> 01:05:44.213
[Mobile vibrates]

1019
01:05:45.793 --> 01:05:48.503
- Yep?
- Why won't your mom pick up?

1020
01:05:49.383 --> 01:05:50.463
[Si-one] <i>Dunno.</i>

1021
01:05:51.133 --> 01:05:53.149
- <i>Is Mom home?</i>
- Nope.

1022
01:05:53.173 --> 01:05:55.383
Did she leave any message?

1023
01:05:56.343 --> 01:05:57.633
Huh.

1024
01:05:58.093 --> 01:06:00.269
[In singsong] Your dad
is going to regret this!

1025
01:06:00.293 --> 01:06:03.019
<i>Your dad is going to regret this!</i>

1026
01:06:03.043 --> 01:06:04.133
[Heavy click]

1027
01:06:06.633 --> 01:06:08.423
Why? Where'd she go?

1028
01:06:09.003 --> 01:06:10.963
[Tender accordion music]

1029
01:06:13.883 --> 01:06:14.979
[He shrieks]

1030
01:06:15.003 --> 01:06:17.649
- Did Mom leave me a costume?
- [Si-one] <i>Yep</i>.

1031
01:06:17.673 --> 01:06:22.043
Can't you answer me in full sentences?

1032
01:06:22.923 --> 01:06:24.689
[Si-one] <i>Good luck. Dad!</i>

1033
01:06:24.713 --> 01:06:25.753
[Annoyed] Thanks!

1034
01:06:29.133 --> 01:06:30.293
[He grunts]

1035
01:06:31.503 --> 01:06:33.713
[Intimate. seductive music]

1036
01:06:45.963 --> 01:06:47.479
Let's dance.

1037
01:06:47.503 --> 01:06:48.503
[She scoffs]

1038
01:06:48.593 --> 01:06:50.399
You don't know the dance.

1039
01:06:50.423 --> 01:06:52.133
Sure I know it.

1040
01:06:53.093 --> 01:06:54.843
I memorized it. watching now.

1041
01:06:56.093 --> 01:06:57.793
You said you practiced a lot.

1042
01:06:59.003 --> 01:07:00.383
Got to show it off.

1043
01:07:20.293 --> 01:07:22.543
[Music halts;
He pants]

1044
01:07:25.383 --> 01:07:29.383
- [Music resumes. faintly]
- Greetings. That way.

1045
01:07:33.963 --> 01:07:36.769
Don't you believe me?

1046
01:07:36.793 --> 01:07:38.149
No. I don't!

1047
01:07:38.173 --> 01:07:40.423
I'm a bullfighter today.
so a pretty bull... no. cow.

1048
01:07:41.383 --> 01:07:42.729
Nice!

1049
01:07:42.753 --> 01:07:45.253
[Busy chatter and laughter]

1050
01:07:56.003 --> 01:07:57.713
Care for a cocktail?

1051
01:08:04.343 --> 01:08:06.883
[Footsteps echo loudly on the dance floor]

1052
01:08:10.463 --> 01:08:12.543
[Music intensifies]

1053
01:08:41.793 --> 01:08:43.633
[They giggle]

1054
01:09:07.253 --> 01:09:09.753
[Music dies down;
Heavy breathing]

1055
01:09:09.843 --> 01:09:12.093
[Frogs ribbit. insects chirp]

1056
01:09:15.593 --> 01:09:17.463
[Heavy breathing continues]

1057
01:09:18.503 --> 01:09:20.793
[Loud thunder;
Heavy rain patters]

1058
01:09:22.423 --> 01:09:24.963
[Faint. fast-paced electronic music
in distance]

1059
01:09:39.383 --> 01:09:41.343
[Music slows down. turns eerie]

1060
01:09:44.173 --> 01:09:45.753
[Music fades]

1061
01:09:47.593 --> 01:09:49.883
[Loud thunder]

1062
01:09:50.713 --> 01:09:52.923
- WELCOME TO GUJONG CITY
- [He sighs]

1063
01:09:55.753 --> 01:09:57.793
[Insects chirp]

1064
01:10:08.253 --> 01:10:10.293
[She sighs]

1065
01:10:11.383 --> 01:10:12.649
[Man-su] Did you fuck
in the car?

1066
01:10:12.673 --> 01:10:14.093
[She startles]

1067
01:10:15.843 --> 01:10:17.439
You like it in the car.

1068
01:10:17.463 --> 01:10:19.883
You wore the black fishnet panties?
Rose lace?

1069
01:10:20.463 --> 01:10:22.173
I searched. and they're missing.

1070
01:10:27.213 --> 01:10:28.343
[Miri] What are you doing?

1071
01:10:31.003 --> 01:10:32.519
[Man-su] You're wearing them!

1072
01:10:32.543 --> 01:10:34.519
You are! Take them off.

1073
01:10:34.543 --> 01:10:37.843
If I smell them.
I'll know if you fucked him or not.

1074
01:10:39.673 --> 01:10:41.253
It'll just take a second!

1075
01:10:42.043 --> 01:10:44.253
If you're innocent.
what are you scared of?

1076
01:10:44.343 --> 01:10:46.293
[She whimpers;
He grunts]

1077
01:10:53.293 --> 01:10:54.503
Did you drink?

1078
01:10:54.923 --> 01:10:55.979
[He scoffs]

1079
01:10:56.003 --> 01:10:57.843
[She sighs]

1080
01:10:58.633 --> 01:11:00.293
You can't!

1081
01:11:01.503 --> 01:11:03.593
We can't go through that again!

1082
01:11:04.383 --> 01:11:06.189
Nine years!

1083
01:11:06.213 --> 01:11:08.979
You've held back nine years.
gritting your teeth.

1084
01:11:09.003 --> 01:11:10.729
Has it gone up in smoke?

1085
01:11:10.753 --> 01:11:13.189
Puking in your sleep. almost suffocating!

1086
01:11:13.213 --> 01:11:14.213
Getting drunk and...

1087
01:11:15.173 --> 01:11:18.713
beating my five-year-old son.
Saying he's jealous of your daughter!

1088
01:11:19.593 --> 01:11:21.093
I've said it a million times.

1089
01:11:21.793 --> 01:11:23.423
Si-one is my kid. too.

1090
01:11:24.133 --> 01:11:25.439
Sure enough.

1091
01:11:25.463 --> 01:11:29.133
You don't discriminate.
You're a dog to everyone when drunk.

1092
01:11:32.253 --> 01:11:34.423
[He barks. aggressively]

1093
01:11:44.673 --> 01:11:45.963
[He moans]

1094
01:11:47.883 --> 01:11:49.963
[She sniffs]

1095
01:11:55.253 --> 01:11:56.713
What were you thinking?

1096
01:11:57.923 --> 01:11:59.899
Matching your costume with Dr Ouch.

1097
01:11:59.923 --> 01:12:01.963
Dressing me up as a goddamn Nutcracker!

1098
01:12:07.383 --> 01:12:08.753
John Smith!

1099
01:12:10.173 --> 01:12:15.439
British Admiral John Smith
and Pocahontas. you idiot!

1100
01:12:15.463 --> 01:12:17.899
Ri-one's favourite cartoon!

1101
01:12:17.923 --> 01:12:20.463
You forgot?
We watched it a million times with her!

1102
01:12:21.343 --> 01:12:23.543
When I told Dr Oh I'd be Pocahontas.

1103
01:12:23.633 --> 01:12:26.793
the whole clinic decided to be
Native Americans!

1104
01:12:26.883 --> 01:12:29.229
The nurse there was dressed as one. too!

1105
01:12:29.253 --> 01:12:33.133
You and I were meant to be a pair!

1106
01:12:34.753 --> 01:12:37.019
You think I'm that kind of person?

1107
01:12:37.043 --> 01:12:38.793
How can you suspect me?

1108
01:12:39.423 --> 01:12:41.269
Sure I can suspect you!

1109
01:12:41.293 --> 01:12:43.729
You're pretty!
You're so damned pretty!

1110
01:12:43.753 --> 01:12:45.133
You're handsome. too!

1111
01:12:48.843 --> 01:12:50.753
What's this? Who did this?

1112
01:12:55.003 --> 01:12:57.753
I'm fighting a war. for our family.

1113
01:12:59.463 --> 01:13:03.463
So we need to band together
and believe each other.

1114
01:13:04.253 --> 01:13:05.503
Loyalty.

1115
01:13:05.593 --> 01:13:06.713
Trust.

1116
01:13:08.093 --> 01:13:10.633
Then why lock yourself in the greenhouse?

1117
01:13:11.213 --> 01:13:12.923
That damned greenhouse!

1118
01:13:13.633 --> 01:13:17.793
And driving 3000km in a month!

1119
01:13:18.713 --> 01:13:19.923
Why bring rubber pants?

1120
01:13:20.543 --> 01:13:23.043
How can you get a snakebite
at a job interview?

1121
01:13:23.133 --> 01:13:25.899
How stupid do you think I am?

1122
01:13:25.923 --> 01:13:27.503
Tell me! Who is she?

1123
01:13:28.003 --> 01:13:30.003
The bitch you go fishing
and eat chicken with.

1124
01:13:30.093 --> 01:13:32.093
having sex smothered in lube oil!

1125
01:13:33.963 --> 01:13:35.883
Honey. don't do this to me.

1126
01:13:36.923 --> 01:13:38.503
My job interviews.

1127
01:13:39.633 --> 01:13:42.343
they're really difficult interviews.

1128
01:13:43.253 --> 01:13:45.793
Looking someone right in the eye.

1129
01:13:46.543 --> 01:13:49.593
- Doing that is really hard.
- [Loud click]

1130
01:13:52.963 --> 01:13:54.543
[She scoffs]

1131
01:13:54.633 --> 01:13:56.003
You don't deny it?

1132
01:13:56.673 --> 01:13:58.923
[High-pitched. unsettling tone]

1133
01:14:00.593 --> 01:14:02.503
[He groans]

1134
01:14:03.963 --> 01:14:06.519
[Tone turns into calm. melancholic music]

1135
01:14:06.543 --> 01:14:08.633
[He breathes heavily. whimpers]

1136
01:14:19.963 --> 01:14:22.043
{\an8}DRINK WITH COLLEAGUES. WORK TALK

1137
01:14:24.003 --> 01:14:25.343
[Salesman] How is this?

1138
01:14:26.463 --> 01:14:28.543
This is a softer material.

1139
01:14:28.633 --> 01:14:30.093
[Customer] Not really.

1140
01:14:33.503 --> 01:14:35.769
[Store door opens;
Melodic door chimes]

1141
01:14:35.793 --> 01:14:36.883
[Salesman] Just a moment.

1142
01:14:37.423 --> 01:14:39.253
Yeni. what is it?

1143
01:14:39.343 --> 01:14:42.423
Can I hang out with my friends
after art lessons?

1144
01:14:46.213 --> 01:14:49.293
- Min's dad will drive you?
- [Yeni] Yes.

1145
01:14:49.383 --> 01:14:50.939
These are no good. either.

1146
01:14:50.963 --> 01:14:52.383
Yes. just a minute.

1147
01:14:53.133 --> 01:14:54.843
I have a pair that you'll like.

1148
01:14:57.463 --> 01:14:58.593
Go on. go!

1149
01:15:00.253 --> 01:15:01.399
It's a brand new item. so...

1150
01:15:01.423 --> 01:15:02.819
- [Melodic chimes]
- Never mind. mister.

1151
01:15:02.843 --> 01:15:04.593
Wait.

1152
01:15:05.963 --> 01:15:07.543
Just a second.

1153
01:15:07.633 --> 01:15:09.543
- Don't go yet.
- [He sighs]

1154
01:15:13.293 --> 01:15:16.883
- Headquarters only sends us a few pairs.
- [Door chimes]

1155
01:15:17.793 --> 01:15:19.213
Just a moment.

1156
01:15:20.133 --> 01:15:21.543
I'll be right there.

1157
01:15:28.463 --> 01:15:30.423
- Sir!
- [Melodic door chimes]

1158
01:15:32.463 --> 01:15:34.463
So the other man left?

1159
01:15:37.253 --> 01:15:38.253
Seems so.

1160
01:15:39.543 --> 01:15:41.423
Sorry to keep you waiting.

1161
01:15:42.253 --> 01:15:44.003
Shoes for yourself?

1162
01:15:44.593 --> 01:15:45.633
Or a gift?

1163
01:15:47.133 --> 01:15:48.729
I've got a daughter. too.

1164
01:15:48.753 --> 01:15:50.253
How old is she?

1165
01:15:52.173 --> 01:15:53.253
Come in.

1166
01:15:53.343 --> 01:15:54.793
[Chimes continue]

1167
01:15:54.883 --> 01:15:55.883
[Man-su] Hmm...

1168
01:16:14.253 --> 01:16:15.503
You miss it. right?

1169
01:16:16.293 --> 01:16:18.793
Having a drink with colleagues.
talking about work?

1170
01:16:20.713 --> 01:16:23.633
It's been over a year for me too.

1171
01:16:24.253 --> 01:16:26.923
so I recognize
an unemployed comrade at once.

1172
01:16:27.963 --> 01:16:30.649
You don't look like a man for this job.

1173
01:16:30.673 --> 01:16:32.479
[Salesman scoffs]

1174
01:16:32.503 --> 01:16:34.043
Ten years old.

1175
01:16:35.293 --> 01:16:36.673
Your daughter!

1176
01:16:37.463 --> 01:16:39.019
What kind of shoes?

1177
01:16:39.043 --> 01:16:40.463
Boots? Sandals?

1178
01:16:41.423 --> 01:16:44.479
- [Man-su] Enamel shoes. Quite shiny.
- Yes.

1179
01:16:44.503 --> 01:16:46.343
I worked in the paper industry.

1180
01:16:47.093 --> 01:16:48.439
Specialty paper.

1181
01:16:48.463 --> 01:16:51.423
We made banknotes. lottery tickets.

1182
01:16:52.343 --> 01:16:54.519
invoices. passports.
ice cream cone sleeves.

1183
01:16:54.543 --> 01:16:57.543
menstrual pad release paper.
cigarette filters.

1184
01:16:57.633 --> 01:16:59.633
People laugh when I say this.

1185
01:17:01.043 --> 01:17:06.463
but for those of us who make it.
white paper is a kind of art.

1186
01:17:08.213 --> 01:17:09.633
Why laugh?

1187
01:17:10.173 --> 01:17:12.173
That feeling of touching fine paper

1188
01:17:13.463 --> 01:17:14.883
is so comforting.

1189
01:17:16.423 --> 01:17:18.423
You've got fine senses. I see.

1190
01:17:19.213 --> 01:17:22.003
My daughter hardly ever speaks.

1191
01:17:23.753 --> 01:17:27.213
When she does.
it's to echo others' words.

1192
01:17:29.543 --> 01:17:32.963
She was born that way.
She only plays cello.

1193
01:17:34.673 --> 01:17:37.253
- Her teacher says she's gifted.
- [Sparse. delicate notes]

1194
01:17:37.343 --> 01:17:40.503
Might even become world famous.

1195
01:17:42.423 --> 01:17:44.673
But she won't play for us.

1196
01:17:45.673 --> 01:17:48.503
As parents. we should support her talent.

1197
01:17:50.003 --> 01:17:52.769
because without music
she'll never be independent.

1198
01:17:52.793 --> 01:17:58.383
Her teacher said she needs
to be playing on a $50.000 cello.

1199
01:17:59.293 --> 01:18:01.793
She'll give a recital this Christmas.

1200
01:18:02.673 --> 01:18:06.253
but she only has rain boots.

1201
01:18:07.133 --> 01:18:11.043
I can't buy her an instrument.
at least I'll get her shoes.

1202
01:18:11.673 --> 01:18:12.843
Wait.

1203
01:18:14.043 --> 01:18:18.253
Her lesson finishes soon.
Maybe I'll bring her to try them on.

1204
01:18:18.343 --> 01:18:19.503
When do you close?

1205
01:18:19.593 --> 01:18:21.269
You can come any time before seven.

1206
01:18:21.293 --> 01:18:23.399
Her lesson won't finish by seven.

1207
01:18:23.423 --> 01:18:25.463
It takes me an hour to clean up.

1208
01:18:26.133 --> 01:18:27.689
I'll wait. then.

1209
01:18:27.713 --> 01:18:29.003
Eight o'clock!

1210
01:18:31.503 --> 01:18:36.503
I can only get a commission
if you buy through me.

1211
01:18:37.043 --> 01:18:38.043
[Man-su] Yes.

1212
01:18:38.633 --> 01:18:41.093
[Melodic door chimes. notes persist]

1213
01:18:44.963 --> 01:18:47.173
[Sparse. delicate notes continue]

1214
01:18:52.383 --> 01:18:54.293
[Water gurgles]

1215
01:18:54.383 --> 01:18:56.713
[Tense. unsettling music;
Hazard button clicks]

1216
01:18:57.543 --> 01:18:58.903
[Man-su whispers] No other choice.

1217
01:19:00.423 --> 01:19:03.503
No other choice.

1218
01:19:03.593 --> 01:19:04.923
No other choice.

1219
01:19:05.543 --> 01:19:06.923
No other choice.

1220
01:19:14.593 --> 01:19:16.293
[Salesman] What are you doing here?

1221
01:19:16.383 --> 01:19:19.293
You haven't been able to
pick up your daughter?

1222
01:19:19.383 --> 01:19:22.793
Think it has to be towed.
It's so expensive. though.

1223
01:19:23.963 --> 01:19:26.883
Then. the money for the shoes.

1224
01:19:28.843 --> 01:19:30.293
[Deep. somber string notes join]

1225
01:19:32.043 --> 01:19:34.189
I'M A MACHINE REPAIRMAN...

1226
01:19:34.213 --> 01:19:37.189
Let's see if my skills are any use.

1227
01:19:37.213 --> 01:19:40.383
My beloved Elantra. no less!

1228
01:19:41.383 --> 01:19:44.293
My. without your glasses.
you look like a model.

1229
01:19:46.463 --> 01:19:48.293
What have we got here?

1230
01:19:49.673 --> 01:19:51.503
[Man-su breathes shakily]

1231
01:19:54.593 --> 01:19:56.423
So this is on your way home.

1232
01:19:58.883 --> 01:20:01.883
[Waves crash loudly;
Music builds slowly]

1233
01:20:03.173 --> 01:20:05.093
So this is it!

1234
01:20:06.883 --> 01:20:08.043
Try starting...

1235
01:20:13.423 --> 01:20:15.593
[Shuddered breathing]

1236
01:20:16.923 --> 01:20:18.003
[Gun clicks. Man-su grunts]

1237
01:20:18.093 --> 01:20:19.713
[Music halts]

1238
01:20:20.293 --> 01:20:22.213
[Gunshot resonates]

1239
01:21:01.383 --> 01:21:03.753
[Warm. gentle acoustic ballad]

1240
01:21:27.923 --> 01:21:30.939
<i>♪ I will walk where my steps take me</i>

1241
01:21:30.963 --> 01:21:34.843
<i>♪ And let the rain wash away
These feelings of mine</i>

1242
01:21:40.383 --> 01:21:43.439
<i>♪ Endlessly. aimlessly</i>

1243
01:21:43.463 --> 01:21:47.213
<i>♪ My heart is floating
Here and there in the rain ♪</i>

1244
01:21:49.003 --> 01:21:50.423
[Volume increases]

1245
01:21:52.793 --> 01:21:55.729
<i>♪ The teddy bear lets out a laugh</i>

1246
01:21:55.753 --> 01:21:58.383
<i>♪ The store lights let out a laugh</i>

1247
01:21:58.753 --> 01:22:01.979
<i>♪ I can't forget the shambles
Of days gone by</i>

1248
01:22:02.003 --> 01:22:04.843
<i>♪ Like the inside of a discarded bag</i>

1249
01:22:09.463 --> 01:22:12.519
<i>♪ I will walk where my steps take me</i>

1250
01:22:12.543 --> 01:22:16.003
<i>♪ And let the rain wash away
These feelings of mine</i>

1251
01:22:16.793 --> 01:22:18.633
[Sirens wail. faintly]

1252
01:22:21.593 --> 01:22:24.543
<i>♪ Endlessly. aimlessly</i>

1253
01:22:24.633 --> 01:22:28.043
<i>♪ My heart is floating
Here and there in the rain</i>

1254
01:22:33.503 --> 01:22:36.769
<i>♪ The passersby don't know</i>

1255
01:22:36.793 --> 01:22:39.543
<i>♪ The lonely street lights don't know</i>

1256
01:22:39.633 --> 01:22:42.439
<i>♪ The dizzying mass of days long gone</i>

1257
01:22:42.463 --> 01:22:46.423
<i>♪ Like a flower bed bursting
Recklessly into bloom</i>

1258
01:22:50.253 --> 01:22:53.229
<i>♪ I will walk where my steps take me</i>

1259
01:22:53.253 --> 01:22:56.963
<i>♪ And let the rain wash away
These feelings of mine</i>

1260
01:23:02.253 --> 01:23:05.149
<i>♪ Endlessly. aimlessly</i>

1261
01:23:05.173 --> 01:23:08.883
<i>♪ My heart is floating
Here and there in the rain ♪</i>

1262
01:23:25.423 --> 01:23:27.093
[He yawns]

1263
01:23:29.003 --> 01:23:31.423
[Birds chirp;
Music continues]

1264
01:23:40.543 --> 01:23:42.979
[Music dies down]

1265
01:23:43.003 --> 01:23:44.343
[Miri. whispering] <i>Honey.</i>

1266
01:23:44.753 --> 01:23:46.133
<i>Honey. Honey!</i>

1267
01:23:46.713 --> 01:23:47.963
[Man-su] Mm?

1268
01:23:50.043 --> 01:23:51.383
The police are here.

1269
01:23:57.003 --> 01:23:58.463
What should we do?

1270
01:24:06.463 --> 01:24:08.753
Be sure not to panic. okay?

1271
01:24:08.843 --> 01:24:10.293
I need to change clothes.

1272
01:24:14.883 --> 01:24:16.923
[Somber. unsettling music;
He gasps]

1273
01:24:19.963 --> 01:24:21.923
I'll explain it all at the station.

1274
01:24:23.883 --> 01:24:25.253
It's all my...

1275
01:24:25.343 --> 01:24:26.543
You Si-one.

1276
01:24:28.043 --> 01:24:30.003
- What were you saying?
- [Bird squawks]

1277
01:24:32.253 --> 01:24:36.173
It's all my fault for being a bad father.

1278
01:24:41.423 --> 01:24:43.633
[Music continues]

1279
01:24:59.843 --> 01:25:01.713
You're the one who said not to panic!

1280
01:25:02.673 --> 01:25:04.479
[Music turns tense. intriguing]

1281
01:25:04.503 --> 01:25:05.713
Get in!

1282
01:25:08.253 --> 01:25:09.543
The door...

1283
01:25:16.503 --> 01:25:18.689
Is Dongho's mom
not picking up on purpose?

1284
01:25:18.713 --> 01:25:20.019
[Line rings]

1285
01:25:20.043 --> 01:25:22.843
How could Dongho
rat on his friend like that?

1286
01:25:23.713 --> 01:25:27.189
It can't have been Si-one's idea.

1287
01:25:27.213 --> 01:25:30.649
It's Dongho's dad's store.
So Dongho suggested it.

1288
01:25:30.673 --> 01:25:31.939
Isn't it obvious?

1289
01:25:31.963 --> 01:25:33.383
DONGHO'S MOM

1290
01:25:33.793 --> 01:25:35.093
[Voicemail answers]

1291
01:25:37.793 --> 01:25:40.753
He must be so lonely
and scared. my baby.

1292
01:25:41.673 --> 01:25:43.003
This is all your fault!

1293
01:25:45.673 --> 01:25:47.253
[Sirens wail in distance]

1294
01:25:47.343 --> 01:25:48.343
Excuse me!

1295
01:25:51.633 --> 01:25:53.793
Just a minute! Wait!

1296
01:25:55.173 --> 01:25:56.293
Hold on a minute!

1297
01:25:57.543 --> 01:26:00.253
Listen. his mother is parking the car.

1298
01:26:00.963 --> 01:26:04.269
Can we go in with him?
He's still just a kid.

1299
01:26:04.293 --> 01:26:06.093
- Alright.
- [Man-su] Thank you.

1300
01:26:07.753 --> 01:26:09.423
Lift your head. Look at me.

1301
01:26:10.503 --> 01:26:13.343
Dongho dragged you into it. right?

1302
01:26:14.043 --> 01:26:15.043
Dongho?

1303
01:26:16.253 --> 01:26:17.689
Why would he drag me...

1304
01:26:17.713 --> 01:26:20.133
[Man-su] Hey. Listen...

1305
01:26:21.633 --> 01:26:26.253
Doing a crime on your own
is incredibly lonely and scary.

1306
01:26:27.093 --> 01:26:29.133
That's how I imagine it. anyway.

1307
01:26:31.673 --> 01:26:33.939
I'll never leave you to feel lonely.

1308
01:26:33.963 --> 01:26:36.189
So. I need your cooperation.

1309
01:26:36.213 --> 01:26:37.753
Since we're a team.

1310
01:26:42.423 --> 01:26:44.729
Actually. the one who suggested it...

1311
01:26:44.753 --> 01:26:47.689
Hey. hey. wait. Wait!

1312
01:26:47.713 --> 01:26:48.793
Get a grip.

1313
01:26:48.883 --> 01:26:50.003
Listen to me.

1314
01:26:50.843 --> 01:26:54.149
- Our family is in a war now.
- What?

1315
01:26:54.173 --> 01:26:56.293
No. I don't mean with each other.

1316
01:26:56.383 --> 01:26:58.503
[He inhales sharply. moans]

1317
01:26:59.543 --> 01:27:04.519
You and me. in this war.
we need to protect our women. right?

1318
01:27:04.543 --> 01:27:07.269
You know Grandpa's pistol?

1319
01:27:07.293 --> 01:27:10.269
Your grandpa bent the fingers
of a dead Viet Cong

1320
01:27:10.293 --> 01:27:12.793
and took that pistol. why do you think?

1321
01:27:14.043 --> 01:27:20.093
To remember that if he hadn't shot first.
the enemy would've shot him with that gun.

1322
01:27:21.173 --> 01:27:22.423
You get what I mean?

1323
01:27:32.093 --> 01:27:34.173
[Ri-one hums]

1324
01:27:35.543 --> 01:27:37.543
[Urine trickles]

1325
01:27:45.593 --> 01:27:47.673
[Woman on TV nearby]

1326
01:27:48.713 --> 01:27:50.633
All the men...

1327
01:27:51.173 --> 01:27:53.503
What'll you do. huh?

1328
01:27:56.343 --> 01:27:58.383
[Toilet flushes]

1329
01:28:02.923 --> 01:28:04.293
Let's wash your hands.

1330
01:28:08.003 --> 01:28:09.003
Up you go!

1331
01:28:12.463 --> 01:28:14.423
[Man puffs]

1332
01:28:15.463 --> 01:28:21.133
Dongho says Si-one wanted to sell
the phones and help out his mom. Damn!

1333
01:28:24.383 --> 01:28:26.463
It's your own store.

1334
01:28:26.963 --> 01:28:28.963
- Let's put this behind us.
- [He scoffs]

1335
01:28:44.633 --> 01:28:47.343
If you don't settle.
he'll get a year's sentence.

1336
01:28:48.213 --> 01:28:51.673
A mom can't let that happen to her son.

1337
01:28:52.543 --> 01:28:53.543
Isn't that so?

1338
01:28:56.133 --> 01:28:57.793
[He mumbles]

1339
01:28:58.423 --> 01:29:00.383
Hey. Man-su.

1340
01:29:01.133 --> 01:29:02.253
[Man-su] Wonno.

1341
01:29:02.713 --> 01:29:03.793
Gimme a smoke.

1342
01:29:04.883 --> 01:29:05.883
Sure.

1343
01:29:07.383 --> 01:29:09.133
What are you doing?

1344
01:29:09.713 --> 01:29:11.713
I started smoking again.

1345
01:29:18.843 --> 01:29:22.253
But honey. mind if I talk
to my friend for a sec?

1346
01:29:23.423 --> 01:29:24.673
Just talk.

1347
01:29:25.543 --> 01:29:26.843
You don't mind. do you?

1348
01:29:28.673 --> 01:29:29.753
[Wonno] Well...

1349
01:29:35.713 --> 01:29:40.543
Dongho dragged Si-one into it.
That's what Dongho will testify.

1350
01:29:41.383 --> 01:29:43.133
Si-one just stood nearby.

1351
01:29:43.883 --> 01:29:45.019
What a crock of shit!

1352
01:29:45.043 --> 01:29:47.503
Dongho turned off the CCTV.

1353
01:29:49.343 --> 01:29:50.713
but not the other one.

1354
01:29:52.633 --> 01:29:55.043
He didn't know to turn off
the security system.

1355
01:29:55.133 --> 01:29:57.439
What if your wife found out

1356
01:29:57.463 --> 01:30:01.439
you use that store at night
as a place for fucking women?

1357
01:30:01.463 --> 01:30:07.463
And if she heard you bragged about it
to all the men in the neighbourhood?

1358
01:30:08.093 --> 01:30:10.923
You jobless stinking piece of shit!

1359
01:30:11.253 --> 01:30:13.503
I'll fucking kill you!

1360
01:30:13.593 --> 01:30:14.593
One more thing.

1361
01:30:15.133 --> 01:30:16.793
You're not buying my home.

1362
01:30:17.793 --> 01:30:19.043
Miri. let's go.

1363
01:30:22.293 --> 01:30:24.019
Forget buying it.

1364
01:30:24.043 --> 01:30:25.633
Honey. be careful.

1365
01:30:31.923 --> 01:30:34.479
Are they up there?

1366
01:30:34.503 --> 01:30:36.253
Are there many?

1367
01:30:39.593 --> 01:30:40.633
How many?

1368
01:30:42.293 --> 01:30:43.293
There's more?

1369
01:30:46.423 --> 01:30:48.003
That brat.

1370
01:30:48.093 --> 01:30:50.543
Two. four. six...

1371
01:30:53.963 --> 01:30:55.963
We don't have to give them back?

1372
01:30:56.593 --> 01:30:58.253
Let's make them disappear.

1373
01:30:58.793 --> 01:31:02.229
Wonno can't help but cover it up anyway.

1374
01:31:02.253 --> 01:31:03.253
Right?

1375
01:31:03.343 --> 01:31:04.343
Of course.

1376
01:31:15.343 --> 01:31:17.213
[Labored breathing]

1377
01:31:19.043 --> 01:31:20.633
What tree will you plant?

1378
01:31:21.213 --> 01:31:23.269
[Man-su] When the apples ripen.
let's make jam.

1379
01:31:23.293 --> 01:31:24.519
[Delicate. uneasy cello notes]

1380
01:31:24.543 --> 01:31:26.899
[Si-one] Will the roots
grow over the phones?

1381
01:31:26.923 --> 01:31:29.253
[Man-su] The tastiest things
grow on filth.

1382
01:31:29.883 --> 01:31:32.043
Fertilizer's made from shit and piss.

1383
01:31:37.423 --> 01:31:39.343
[In English] Okay. thank you.

1384
01:31:41.463 --> 01:31:44.093
[In Korean] Is it true about Grandpa?

1385
01:31:45.503 --> 01:31:47.543
He hanged himself in this house?

1386
01:31:51.713 --> 01:31:52.963
You know his pig farm?

1387
01:31:54.463 --> 01:31:55.593
They caught a disease.

1388
01:31:56.593 --> 01:31:59.229
and he had to kill them all.
20.000 pigs.

1389
01:31:59.253 --> 01:32:01.649
- [He gasps]
- [Si-one] How?

1390
01:32:01.673 --> 01:32:03.253
He buried them. alive.

1391
01:32:04.673 --> 01:32:07.649
But he was always a bit unstable.

1392
01:32:07.673 --> 01:32:09.593
Ever since fighting in Vietnam.

1393
01:32:10.173 --> 01:32:15.503
In the old barn. he...
you know. but I didn't see it.

1394
01:32:15.593 --> 01:32:17.253
[Wind rustles]

1395
01:32:17.343 --> 01:32:18.979
Hey.

1396
01:32:19.003 --> 01:32:21.253
[Cello notes continue]

1397
01:32:23.633 --> 01:32:24.963
[He whispers] Sit with me.

1398
01:32:25.503 --> 01:32:27.923
- Come closer.
- [Suspenseful. jazz-like music]

1399
01:32:35.343 --> 01:32:36.593
Mom doesn't know.

1400
01:32:37.793 --> 01:32:39.043
Don't look. don't look!

1401
01:32:41.213 --> 01:32:42.293
I quit.

1402
01:32:44.543 --> 01:32:45.883
Throw them out yourself.

1403
01:32:54.133 --> 01:32:57.173
[Music builds slowly;
Birds and insects chirp]

1404
01:33:31.883 --> 01:33:33.939
[Muffled cough]

1405
01:33:33.963 --> 01:33:36.843
[Mumbles and exhales in pleasure]

1406
01:33:57.173 --> 01:33:59.293
[Music swells]

1407
01:34:15.133 --> 01:34:17.253
[Chainsaw whirs. loudly]

1408
01:34:19.133 --> 01:34:21.133
[Music settles. lingers]

1409
01:34:21.963 --> 01:34:23.963
[Whirring stops]

1410
01:34:29.633 --> 01:34:31.633
[He breathes shakily]

1411
01:34:32.843 --> 01:34:35.213
[Whirring resumes]

1412
01:34:38.253 --> 01:34:40.383
[He sobs softly]

1413
01:35:17.793 --> 01:35:20.173
[Music continues]

1414
01:35:38.713 --> 01:35:40.883
[Music swells]

1415
01:36:13.423 --> 01:36:15.543
[Soft whimpering and squelching]

1416
01:36:16.753 --> 01:36:18.713
[Water gurgles]

1417
01:36:21.093 --> 01:36:22.753
[Music dies down]

1418
01:36:22.843 --> 01:36:23.843
[Detective] Papyrus.

1419
01:36:25.043 --> 01:36:26.463
You interviewed there?

1420
01:36:28.503 --> 01:36:29.503
I was rejected.

1421
01:36:29.593 --> 01:36:30.793
The name Go Sijo...

1422
01:36:30.883 --> 01:36:32.293
Never heard of it.

1423
01:36:36.383 --> 01:36:38.383
[Pen scribbles on paper]

1424
01:36:39.043 --> 01:36:40.463
And Gu Bummo?

1425
01:36:47.713 --> 01:36:49.519
Not sure.

1426
01:36:49.543 --> 01:36:51.843
We're visiting people
who interviewed there.

1427
01:36:52.383 --> 01:36:54.503
Anything unusual happen recently?

1428
01:36:54.593 --> 01:36:56.253
Have you felt in danger?

1429
01:37:00.543 --> 01:37:02.793
Those two men have disappeared.

1430
01:37:03.383 --> 01:37:04.503
[Deep exhale]

1431
01:37:05.923 --> 01:37:07.399
You may think badly of me.

1432
01:37:07.423 --> 01:37:09.843
but even after hearing they died.

1433
01:37:10.503 --> 01:37:15.399
the thought that comes to mind is.
I wonder what lucky person got hired?

1434
01:37:15.423 --> 01:37:16.793
I said "disappeared."

1435
01:37:17.883 --> 01:37:20.769
Give me that.
And then.

1436
01:37:20.793 --> 01:37:26.593
Mr You. you said to me.
"they died".

1437
01:37:28.093 --> 01:37:29.793
Why do you think they're dead?

1438
01:37:30.883 --> 01:37:32.133
Well.

1439
01:37:33.633 --> 01:37:36.543
In today's world. if someone disappears.

1440
01:37:37.043 --> 01:37:38.133
then usually...

1441
01:37:40.133 --> 01:37:45.479
"In today's world. if someone
disappears. then usually..."

1442
01:37:45.503 --> 01:37:49.229
Go Sijo's wife reported him missing.

1443
01:37:49.253 --> 01:37:53.229
and after tracking his phone.
we found his car sitting by itself.

1444
01:37:53.253 --> 01:37:56.439
She said after being fired.
he was extremely depressed.

1445
01:37:56.463 --> 01:37:57.519
Oh my.

1446
01:37:57.543 --> 01:38:00.673
A phone contains
all of a person's life. right?

1447
01:38:01.253 --> 01:38:04.479
Who you talked to. and also.

1448
01:38:04.503 --> 01:38:06.109
- <i>who you couldn't talk to.</i>
- [Rain patters]

1449
01:38:06.133 --> 01:38:07.649
- NINE MISSED CALLS
- [Mobile rings]

1450
01:38:07.673 --> 01:38:09.093
What the!

1451
01:38:12.963 --> 01:38:15.173
It's that number! The missed calls.

1452
01:38:16.003 --> 01:38:17.343
Umbrella.

1453
01:38:18.213 --> 01:38:19.883
Finally. you answered.

1454
01:38:20.383 --> 01:38:24.003
You've called the phone of a man
who's gone missing.

1455
01:38:24.093 --> 01:38:25.963
Excuse me. but who are you?

1456
01:38:26.883 --> 01:38:29.479
I'm head of HR at Papyrus.

1457
01:38:29.503 --> 01:38:33.793
Mr Go interviewed at our company.
and I called to say he was hired.

1458
01:38:33.883 --> 01:38:35.793
This is like some kind of curse.

1459
01:38:35.883 --> 01:38:36.939
[Detective 2] <i>What?</i>

1460
01:38:36.963 --> 01:38:43.649
We originally planned to hire a different
applicant but couldn't reach him. either.

1461
01:38:43.673 --> 01:38:45.753
[Detective 2] <i>What was that man's name?</i>

1462
01:38:45.843 --> 01:38:49.543
That man... hold on. his name...

1463
01:38:50.173 --> 01:38:51.503
He scored highest.

1464
01:38:51.593 --> 01:38:54.189
Gu... Gu... Gu...

1465
01:38:54.213 --> 01:38:55.633
Bummo.

1466
01:38:56.213 --> 01:38:59.503
And I knew I'd seen that name before.

1467
01:39:00.213 --> 01:39:01.213
GU BUMMO

1468
01:39:02.293 --> 01:39:03.543
Look. kiddo!

1469
01:39:06.463 --> 01:39:08.213
They knew each other?

1470
01:39:10.463 --> 01:39:13.479
So. there were two paper men.

1471
01:39:13.503 --> 01:39:16.979
They knew each other.
And disappeared at the same time.

1472
01:39:17.003 --> 01:39:19.769
We did a painstaking search
around the car.

1473
01:39:19.793 --> 01:39:21.939
We found traces of Mr Go's blood...

1474
01:39:21.963 --> 01:39:22.963
Blood.

1475
01:39:23.753 --> 01:39:28.343
And what might've caused
Mr Go's blood to spill out of his veins?

1476
01:39:29.043 --> 01:39:30.543
A gun.
A handgun.

1477
01:39:30.633 --> 01:39:32.173
Made in North Korea.

1478
01:39:32.923 --> 01:39:34.729
- A bullet shell was found.
- [He gasps]

1479
01:39:34.753 --> 01:39:36.093
By me.

1480
01:39:36.543 --> 01:39:37.843
<i>A bullet shell!</i>

1481
01:39:39.883 --> 01:39:41.883
[Soft rattle]

1482
01:39:43.633 --> 01:39:44.673
Pretty scary.

1483
01:39:45.343 --> 01:39:47.149
[Melancholic cello music
plays on speaker]

1484
01:39:47.173 --> 01:39:51.093
Until I catch the culprit.
you must be very careful.

1485
01:39:54.543 --> 01:39:56.149
[Man-su] Ri-one.

1486
01:39:56.173 --> 01:39:58.383
[Detective 2] What kid
listens to such music?

1487
01:39:59.883 --> 01:40:02.293
I'll contact you as soon as I go missing.

1488
01:40:03.503 --> 01:40:04.883
[Nervous chuckle]

1489
01:40:09.843 --> 01:40:12.463
[Detective 2] This is not a joking matter.

1490
01:40:13.343 --> 01:40:14.343
Drive safely!

1491
01:40:15.133 --> 01:40:16.229
Ri-one!

1492
01:40:16.253 --> 01:40:17.293
What are you doing?

1493
01:40:17.383 --> 01:40:19.093
[Fence squeaks. closes]

1494
01:40:22.293 --> 01:40:23.753
What's wrong?

1495
01:40:23.843 --> 01:40:25.253
My dear Ri-one.

1496
01:40:26.753 --> 01:40:28.253
Don't cry. Don't cry.

1497
01:40:29.963 --> 01:40:31.149
Don't cry.

1498
01:40:31.173 --> 01:40:34.593
I'll bring them back. okay?
Stop crying.

1499
01:40:36.753 --> 01:40:38.673
Just need to do one more.

1500
01:40:38.793 --> 01:40:39.899
[Music concludes]

1501
01:40:39.923 --> 01:40:41.503
25 YEARS

1502
01:40:54.503 --> 01:40:56.963
[Sentimental Korean pop ballad]

1503
01:41:00.423 --> 01:41:02.593
<i>♪ After you left me ♪</i>

1504
01:41:03.343 --> 01:41:09.213
[He sings along] <i>♪ The hole you left
In my chest hurts me so much!</i>

1505
01:41:10.293 --> 01:41:14.253
<i>♪ Thinking I will die. I pray</i>

1506
01:41:15.253 --> 01:41:19.093
<i>♪ Please take this pain from me... ♪</i>

1507
01:41:20.843 --> 01:41:22.123
[Tires screech. Sun-chul grunts]

1508
01:41:23.213 --> 01:41:24.753
What the fuck?

1509
01:41:26.503 --> 01:41:28.003
Mr Choi Sun-chul?

1510
01:41:28.093 --> 01:41:29.753
You thought I was a deer?

1511
01:41:30.423 --> 01:41:32.293
- For fuck's sake.
- I waited all day.

1512
01:41:32.383 --> 01:41:35.043
- I'm You Man-su.
- [Music subsides]

1513
01:41:35.843 --> 01:41:38.963
I was manager of specialty paper
at Solar until they fired me.

1514
01:41:40.423 --> 01:41:41.463
[Car whirs]

1515
01:41:44.173 --> 01:41:46.939
The guy from the restroom?

1516
01:41:46.963 --> 01:41:50.503
I've got all this free time.
and I envy you so much.

1517
01:41:50.593 --> 01:41:54.293
I've been watching
your Instagram every day.

1518
01:41:54.383 --> 01:41:55.423
Whoa.

1519
01:41:56.043 --> 01:41:57.729
You mean I'm being stalked?

1520
01:41:57.753 --> 01:42:01.593
Want to have a drink with me?

1521
01:42:02.543 --> 01:42:03.649
[He sniffles]

1522
01:42:03.673 --> 01:42:05.343
Seems like you already had some.

1523
01:42:07.503 --> 01:42:08.503
Alright.

1524
01:42:10.343 --> 01:42:12.463
[Plucky. inquisitive music]

1525
01:42:13.753 --> 01:42:15.729
After slaving for 25 years.

1526
01:42:15.753 --> 01:42:18.133
they gave me 25 minutes to clear out.

1527
01:42:18.923 --> 01:42:20.269
I walk out of the office.

1528
01:42:20.293 --> 01:42:24.519
and the security guard
had my things in a box already

1529
01:42:24.543 --> 01:42:26.843
and was standing there. holding it.

1530
01:42:27.503 --> 01:42:31.979
They wouldn't let me go down
the hallway where I'd always walked.

1531
01:42:32.003 --> 01:42:33.689
[Sun-chul] Sent you out the back door?

1532
01:42:33.713 --> 01:42:34.769
[Man-su] Exactly.

1533
01:42:34.793 --> 01:42:36.343
[Sun-chul] Fucking dickwads!

1534
01:42:37.293 --> 01:42:38.729
Hurry up and eat.

1535
01:42:38.753 --> 01:42:40.923
[Music continues]

1536
01:42:42.633 --> 01:42:45.093
[Ri-one hums]

1537
01:43:01.633 --> 01:43:02.769
[Miri] Not again!

1538
01:43:02.793 --> 01:43:04.963
If you don't eat.
I'll take that paper away!

1539
01:43:06.673 --> 01:43:10.883
You need to eat. so your arms get strong.
and your bowing gets stronger.

1540
01:43:13.173 --> 01:43:15.543
[Music continues]

1541
01:43:15.633 --> 01:43:19.883
Why are the men in this house
all hiding something from me. Ri-one?

1542
01:43:20.383 --> 01:43:21.793
Why could it be?

1543
01:43:22.293 --> 01:43:24.383
Do they want to die?

1544
01:43:25.173 --> 01:43:29.593
- My quality ratio was 96%.
- [Music dies down]

1545
01:43:30.293 --> 01:43:32.793
On those old Bumin machines.

1546
01:43:34.423 --> 01:43:38.593
They don't give out Pulp Man of the Year
to any old fool.

1547
01:43:39.293 --> 01:43:40.713
Hey. eat up. Eat this.

1548
01:43:42.423 --> 01:43:43.423
Right.

1549
01:43:44.673 --> 01:43:47.543
If they gave it to any old fool.
I'd have gotten one.

1550
01:43:49.383 --> 01:43:52.593
Hey. that's not what I meant!

1551
01:43:54.463 --> 01:43:55.883
Sorry. fuck.

1552
01:43:56.503 --> 01:43:58.253
Damn it. drink up.

1553
01:44:00.133 --> 01:44:01.383
"Fuck"?

1554
01:44:02.043 --> 01:44:03.213
No. I...

1555
01:44:05.883 --> 01:44:07.963
[Manic laughter]

1556
01:44:10.213 --> 01:44:12.439
Hey! Listen to you.

1557
01:44:12.463 --> 01:44:14.769
I fucking love it. fuck!

1558
01:44:14.793 --> 01:44:17.093
- Have a fucking drink!
- [Sun-chul] Let's fucking drink!

1559
01:44:22.543 --> 01:44:24.503
[He hisses]

1560
01:44:25.673 --> 01:44:28.133
[Man-su] Hey. slow down a bit.

1561
01:44:29.883 --> 01:44:31.883
[Sun-chul] To hell with that.
I'm drinking fast.

1562
01:44:33.923 --> 01:44:35.593
Do they want to die?

1563
01:44:39.003 --> 01:44:41.593
So you saw it.
or you think you saw it?

1564
01:44:47.543 --> 01:44:50.593
I'll die if I keep working like this.

1565
01:44:51.463 --> 01:44:56.293
With this much work to do.
I need another manager.

1566
01:44:58.253 --> 01:45:00.253
[Anticipatory. suggestive music]

1567
01:45:01.753 --> 01:45:03.003
Right.

1568
01:45:05.383 --> 01:45:06.543
At your level!

1569
01:45:06.633 --> 01:45:08.543
That's what I'm saying!

1570
01:45:12.043 --> 01:45:13.963
Man-su my man. you crying?

1571
01:45:17.253 --> 01:45:19.543
- Feel sorry for me?
- [Man-su chuckles]

1572
01:45:23.793 --> 01:45:25.503
Why so soft-hearted?

1573
01:45:28.213 --> 01:45:29.593
Ask the higher-ups.

1574
01:45:30.343 --> 01:45:31.343
Ask what?

1575
01:45:34.253 --> 01:45:35.923
Ask them to hire someone else!

1576
01:45:37.213 --> 01:45:38.793
Those tight-assed pricks?

1577
01:45:39.843 --> 01:45:42.229
If you sit tight.
their asses get tighter!

1578
01:45:42.253 --> 01:45:43.899
Demand it!

1579
01:45:43.923 --> 01:45:45.593
Just collapse at work one day!

1580
01:45:46.133 --> 01:45:48.503
You'll need sick leave!
Production will stop!

1581
01:45:49.213 --> 01:45:51.383
Won't they come to their senses then?

1582
01:45:54.293 --> 01:45:57.899
Come to their senses?
They'll just fire me.

1583
01:45:57.923 --> 01:45:59.383
Recommend me.

1584
01:46:00.043 --> 01:46:03.383
We'd work really well together!
Complementing each other.

1585
01:46:04.593 --> 01:46:05.793
A Team. B Team.

1586
01:46:08.383 --> 01:46:09.713
Sure.

1587
01:46:10.963 --> 01:46:12.593
I'll try talking to them.

1588
01:46:14.383 --> 01:46:16.593
[Music swells]

1589
01:46:19.793 --> 01:46:22.093
[Music halts. resonates]

1590
01:46:26.093 --> 01:46:27.213
<i>Oh dear.</i>

1591
01:46:28.593 --> 01:46:30.503
So this is the best you got?

1592
01:46:32.293 --> 01:46:35.293
[Sun-chul] I know. water streaks.

1593
01:46:36.673 --> 01:46:41.253
It's the cross-link cellulose recipe
of those bastards at Bumin.

1594
01:46:41.343 --> 01:46:42.503
But you know.

1595
01:46:44.843 --> 01:46:47.439
I've got no other choice.

1596
01:46:47.463 --> 01:46:50.003
Even if you use their machines.

1597
01:46:50.093 --> 01:46:52.439
you don't have to use their recipe. too.

1598
01:46:52.463 --> 01:46:56.399
How can you afford this house
as a line manager? And that car?

1599
01:46:56.423 --> 01:47:00.503
Someone might think you're
pocketing all kinds of cash.

1600
01:47:01.923 --> 01:47:04.043
That's not what I think.

1601
01:47:04.133 --> 01:47:07.293
but others might think that way. I mean.

1602
01:47:09.213 --> 01:47:11.213
I really don't think that. Here.

1603
01:47:13.423 --> 01:47:14.543
Bottoms up.

1604
01:47:24.253 --> 01:47:25.293
You okay?

1605
01:47:39.793 --> 01:47:41.543
[Sun-chul] You're dead now.

1606
01:47:46.383 --> 01:47:48.503
[Glass clinks]

1607
01:47:54.593 --> 01:47:55.923
Bomb shots. okay?

1608
01:48:16.543 --> 01:48:18.503
[Glass clinks. beer fizzes]

1609
01:48:26.463 --> 01:48:27.923
[He inhales deeply]

1610
01:48:32.293 --> 01:48:34.189
[Man-su] <i>No other choice.
No other choice.</i>

1611
01:48:34.213 --> 01:48:35.503
No other choice.

1612
01:48:36.543 --> 01:48:38.503
No other choice.

1613
01:48:40.043 --> 01:48:42.383
Hurry the fuck up!

1614
01:48:58.133 --> 01:48:59.133
[He gulps]

1615
01:49:00.793 --> 01:49:03.019
[Loud gulps]

1616
01:49:03.043 --> 01:49:05.173
[Muffled breathing]

1617
01:49:12.423 --> 01:49:14.343
[Glass clinks]

1618
01:49:16.213 --> 01:49:17.399
[Deep exhalation]

1619
01:49:17.423 --> 01:49:19.713
[Glass clinks]

1620
01:49:28.673 --> 01:49:30.753
[He hisses]

1621
01:49:32.173 --> 01:49:33.713
[Loud burp]

1622
01:49:40.003 --> 01:49:41.463
[Sun-chul] So freaking cold.

1623
01:49:43.423 --> 01:49:44.753
- My head.
- [Man-su sighs]

1624
01:49:44.843 --> 01:49:47.213
[Elegant. melancholic classical music]

1625
01:49:52.713 --> 01:49:54.343
[Man-su] Where do you keep the...?

1626
01:50:15.463 --> 01:50:17.503
[He grunts]

1627
01:50:21.713 --> 01:50:23.843
[Sun-chul screams;
Man-su groans]

1628
01:50:36.503 --> 01:50:39.093
What a fucking relief!

1629
01:50:41.883 --> 01:50:43.883
[Music continues]

1630
01:50:44.543 --> 01:50:47.189
I need some fucking air!

1631
01:50:47.213 --> 01:50:48.689
Let's go out.

1632
01:50:48.713 --> 01:50:53.173
Getting drunk in front of a bonfire
is my lifelong dream!

1633
01:50:53.843 --> 01:50:55.729
[Sun-chul] You're freaking awesome.

1634
01:50:55.753 --> 01:50:56.923
Vodka.

1635
01:50:57.963 --> 01:51:00.019
[They laugh]

1636
01:51:00.043 --> 01:51:02.213
You had more?

1637
01:51:03.383 --> 01:51:04.713
Man-superman.

1638
01:51:05.343 --> 01:51:06.923
you're the best!

1639
01:51:13.963 --> 01:51:16.043
[Music concludes]

1640
01:51:16.133 --> 01:51:18.043
[Insects chirp]

1641
01:51:23.293 --> 01:51:28.043
I moved here six months ago
and it's my first fucking bonfire.

1642
01:51:30.293 --> 01:51:35.463
I thought I'd have barbecue every day.

1643
01:51:36.463 --> 01:51:39.883
When you get the thing you want.
that's what happens.

1644
01:51:41.343 --> 01:51:43.593
My wife was right.

1645
01:51:47.753 --> 01:51:51.003
[Man-su] I really don't want to do this.

1646
01:51:51.093 --> 01:51:52.093
What?

1647
01:51:53.343 --> 01:51:57.383
But if I don't. the deaths of
those other two are meaningless.

1648
01:51:58.963 --> 01:52:00.173
Just a dog's death.

1649
01:52:01.673 --> 01:52:03.383
No...

1650
01:52:04.383 --> 01:52:07.173
You shouldn't barbecue dogs!

1651
01:52:08.963 --> 01:52:11.213
[Labored breathing]

1652
01:52:25.093 --> 01:52:27.213
[Labored breathing]

1653
01:52:30.253 --> 01:52:32.463
[He snores]

1654
01:52:39.883 --> 01:52:43.213
[Shovels thud against soil]

1655
01:52:46.713 --> 01:52:48.213
[Sharp breath]

1656
01:52:49.633 --> 01:52:51.649
[Deep whoosh]

1657
01:52:51.673 --> 01:52:53.713
[Chainsaw whirs. faintly]

1658
01:52:54.963 --> 01:52:56.923
[Whirring fades]

1659
01:53:29.923 --> 01:53:31.963
[Soft rustle]

1660
01:53:35.843 --> 01:53:37.963
[She breathes heavily]

1661
01:54:08.293 --> 01:54:10.383
[Mobile vibrates]

1662
01:54:15.713 --> 01:54:18.093
MS WIFE

1663
01:54:28.923 --> 01:54:32.003
Sorry. I can't turn on the video.

1664
01:54:32.093 --> 01:54:34.543
It's okay. You look at me.

1665
01:54:34.633 --> 01:54:37.229
<i>I didn't want to get your hopes up.</i>

1666
01:54:37.253 --> 01:54:39.383
<i>but I'm visiting a friend from Moon Paper.</i>

1667
01:54:42.793 --> 01:54:47.479
He's got so much work.
the company needs another line manager.

1668
01:54:47.503 --> 01:54:49.543
Remember what the detectives said?

1669
01:54:49.633 --> 01:54:51.673
- About the interviewees.
- [Man-su] <i>Yeah.</i>

1670
01:54:52.883 --> 01:54:53.883
That they died.

1671
01:54:54.633 --> 01:54:55.633
Yeah?

1672
01:54:58.883 --> 01:54:59.883
So?

1673
01:55:01.793 --> 01:55:03.003
I'm worried.

1674
01:55:03.793 --> 01:55:07.633
- You go around late at night...
- Hey. I'm okay.

1675
01:55:08.963 --> 01:55:10.939
How can you be so sure?

1676
01:55:10.963 --> 01:55:12.133
Because I'm...

1677
01:55:13.673 --> 01:55:14.963
me?

1678
01:55:16.383 --> 01:55:19.293
Hey. can't you drop that
and come home now?

1679
01:55:20.213 --> 01:55:22.939
[Man-su] <i>I don't want to say this. but no.</i>

1680
01:55:22.963 --> 01:55:25.043
Don't carry the load by yourself.

1681
01:55:25.133 --> 01:55:27.439
Even a sheet of paper
is better lifted together.

1682
01:55:27.463 --> 01:55:31.293
[Man-su] <i>That's a favourite saying
in our industry. A sheet of paper.</i>

1683
01:55:32.093 --> 01:55:35.003
If the four of us band together.
we can beat this.

1684
01:55:35.093 --> 01:55:36.149
[Man-su] <i>Six.</i>

1685
01:55:36.173 --> 01:55:38.899
I know. Si-two Ri-two.

1686
01:55:38.923 --> 01:55:40.793
I'm going to bring them back.

1687
01:55:40.883 --> 01:55:43.753
You'd be good at gardening
or bonsai. too.

1688
01:55:44.383 --> 01:55:47.253
People live to 100. you have time.

1689
01:55:47.343 --> 01:55:49.689
- This is my last interview.
- [Sun-chul grunts. muffled]

1690
01:55:49.713 --> 01:55:53.293
<i>Up until now I've been digging.
now I need to plant the tree.</i>

1691
01:55:53.383 --> 01:55:56.253
If you do something bad.

1692
01:55:56.753 --> 01:55:59.423
I'm doing it with you. okay?

1693
01:56:04.503 --> 01:56:07.133
Hey. don't worry.

1694
01:56:08.793 --> 01:56:10.423
I think my friend woke up.

1695
01:56:10.963 --> 01:56:13.729
- <i>Your cheek...</i>
- I'll call tomorrow. okay? Bye.

1696
01:56:13.753 --> 01:56:14.793
<i>Honey!</i>

1697
01:56:19.133 --> 01:56:20.689
[Shuddered breathing]

1698
01:56:20.713 --> 01:56:22.843
[Delicate. melancholic. string music]

1699
01:56:42.463 --> 01:56:44.543
[Strained breathing. gurgling]

1700
01:57:02.343 --> 01:57:04.543
[Sun-chul retches]

1701
01:57:17.343 --> 01:57:19.253
[Music dies down]

1702
01:57:19.343 --> 01:57:21.543
[Faint chainsaw whirring;
He moans. sleepily]

1703
01:57:21.633 --> 01:57:23.253
[Miri] Si-one. Si-one!

1704
01:57:24.043 --> 01:57:26.293
- It's okay.
- [Whirring fades]

1705
01:57:26.383 --> 01:57:28.463
[Si-one breathes heavily]

1706
01:57:29.343 --> 01:57:31.003
I dug in the ground.

1707
01:57:32.253 --> 01:57:33.293
There?

1708
01:57:33.843 --> 01:57:35.633
There really was something.

1709
01:57:38.593 --> 01:57:39.793
He cut up a pig?

1710
01:57:39.883 --> 01:57:41.213
Yes.

1711
01:57:48.673 --> 01:57:51.253
[Si-one] Like when he barbecued
a pig for us last year?

1712
01:57:52.423 --> 01:57:55.519
He put a whole pig in the ground
to fertilize the tree.

1713
01:57:55.543 --> 01:57:57.463
Must've been so tough for him.

1714
01:57:58.093 --> 01:58:00.423
<i>So that's what it was.</i>

1715
01:58:01.003 --> 01:58:02.173
<i>a pig.</i>

1716
01:58:16.423 --> 01:58:18.633
[Birds squawk]

1717
01:58:50.463 --> 01:58:52.593
[Wind rustles]

1718
01:59:02.343 --> 01:59:04.923
[Music plays Mozart's
elegant Piano Concerto No. 23]

1719
01:59:25.003 --> 01:59:26.713
Did the interview go well?

1720
01:59:29.293 --> 01:59:30.293
Yeah.

1721
01:59:32.463 --> 01:59:33.543
Did you sleep well?

1722
01:59:49.593 --> 01:59:51.673
[Sighs with relief]

1723
01:59:52.293 --> 01:59:53.713
Just one minute.

1724
01:59:56.843 --> 02:00:01.479
Fifty-nine. fifty-eight. fifty-seven...

1725
02:00:01.503 --> 02:00:03.593
Count up. not down.

1726
02:00:05.343 --> 02:00:11.753
One. two. three. four...

1727
02:00:11.843 --> 02:00:14.149
[Music continues]

1728
02:00:14.173 --> 02:00:16.463
So you drank. in the end.

1729
02:00:17.093 --> 02:00:18.173
[Man-su] Yeah.

1730
02:00:19.793 --> 02:00:21.729
You smell of smoke. too.

1731
02:00:21.753 --> 02:00:24.043
We had a barbecue at my friend's place.

1732
02:00:24.923 --> 02:00:27.843
He's been on his own six months.
but he's lonely already.

1733
02:00:29.093 --> 02:00:30.729
Divorced?

1734
02:00:30.753 --> 02:00:32.923
They split up because of the house.

1735
02:00:33.923 --> 02:00:37.899
He wanted to live in nature.
but she refused.

1736
02:00:37.923 --> 02:00:40.519
Can that be a reason?

1737
02:00:40.543 --> 02:00:42.043
[She scoffs]

1738
02:00:42.133 --> 02:00:43.633
Splitting up over that?

1739
02:00:47.793 --> 02:00:48.923
I'm sorry.

1740
02:00:49.543 --> 02:00:54.293
When I was doing my degree.
I couldn't have fun with you.

1741
02:00:56.923 --> 02:01:01.173
You shouldn't have lived so hard.

1742
02:01:05.343 --> 02:01:07.713
[Music swells]

1743
02:01:14.423 --> 02:01:16.543
How many seconds? Thirty?

1744
02:01:22.043 --> 02:01:23.343
Fifty-nine.

1745
02:01:24.463 --> 02:01:25.593
Sixty.

1746
02:01:33.173 --> 02:01:34.843
[Men laugh;
Music continues]

1747
02:01:36.883 --> 02:01:39.173
[Interviewer] That must've been hard
for you.

1748
02:01:40.003 --> 02:01:46.019
So what I realised
while going through that ordeal

1749
02:01:46.043 --> 02:01:47.793
<i>is you need a creative plan.</i>

1750
02:01:47.883 --> 02:01:51.189
<i>The important thing
is to shift your perspective.</i>

1751
02:01:51.213 --> 02:01:54.229
<i>In the execution phase.
you have to be persistent and bold.</i>

1752
02:01:54.253 --> 02:01:58.293
<i>When necessary. at any time
you need to be able to say no.</i>

1753
02:01:58.383 --> 02:02:00.383
[Clock ticks]

1754
02:02:09.713 --> 02:02:11.729
[Interviewer 2] We have
a "lights-out system."

1755
02:02:11.753 --> 02:02:15.189
Recently we built
a fully automated factory.

1756
02:02:15.213 --> 02:02:16.399
Lights out?

1757
02:02:16.423 --> 02:02:19.979
- Since AI doesn't need lights turned on.
- [Man-su] Right.

1758
02:02:20.003 --> 02:02:24.399
The days of tapping a roll
with a stick are over.

1759
02:02:24.423 --> 02:02:26.293
Yes. of course.

1760
02:02:26.383 --> 02:02:28.963
[Interviewer 3] Anyway.
we quite urgently need you

1761
02:02:29.633 --> 02:02:31.043
to oversee this test run.

1762
02:02:32.633 --> 02:02:36.343
When you say fully automated.
the workers...

1763
02:02:36.963 --> 02:02:39.213
will have to be reduced. right?

1764
02:02:39.753 --> 02:02:43.093
That's the whole point of the system.
No other choice.

1765
02:02:43.793 --> 02:02:45.963
Do you have any objection?

1766
02:02:46.963 --> 02:02:49.213
[Music continues]

1767
02:02:52.883 --> 02:02:55.503
If you don't like it. you can say no.

1768
02:02:56.543 --> 02:02:57.729
Not at all.

1769
02:02:57.753 --> 02:03:00.133
How can you go against the times?

1770
02:03:00.883 --> 02:03:07.253
But at any rate. you need one person
to watch over it all. right?

1771
02:03:08.963 --> 02:03:11.133
[Music concludes;
Birds chirp]

1772
02:03:11.673 --> 02:03:13.689
[Detective] So five years ago.

1773
02:03:13.713 --> 02:03:16.399
there was a secret bid
at Minting and Security Printing Corp?

1774
02:03:16.423 --> 02:03:22.543
Yes. the competition was fierce then.

1775
02:03:23.883 --> 02:03:28.293
Solar. where I worked. was one of
the three designated companies.

1776
02:03:28.923 --> 02:03:32.003
We never even considered bidding.

1777
02:03:33.133 --> 02:03:34.793
Then who made the bid?

1778
02:03:35.423 --> 02:03:39.649
Two people facing off as representatives
of the two major paper companies.

1779
02:03:39.673 --> 02:03:44.343
Who were the rivals
in this bloody bidding war?

1780
02:03:47.463 --> 02:03:49.269
[Detective] Gu Bummo and...

1781
02:03:49.293 --> 02:03:50.979
- [Detective 2] Go Sijo!
- [He gasps]

1782
02:03:51.003 --> 02:03:53.503
The day he returned
from his business trip to Daejeon...

1783
02:03:53.593 --> 02:03:54.769
[Soft. suggestive music]

1784
02:03:54.793 --> 02:03:57.713
His sleep-talking woke me up
in the middle of the night.

1785
02:03:59.503 --> 02:04:03.043
He started crying and whining.

1786
02:04:05.213 --> 02:04:09.423
saying things like. "It's not fair!"
and "Don't insult me!"

1787
02:04:11.503 --> 02:04:12.673
Then after that.

1788
02:04:13.883 --> 02:04:15.253
wouldn't you know...

1789
02:04:16.043 --> 02:04:18.043
[She mimics snoring]

1790
02:04:19.503 --> 02:04:21.253
He was surely asleep.

1791
02:04:22.003 --> 02:04:24.753
but he gathered the phlegm
in his mouth and...

1792
02:04:31.043 --> 02:04:33.769
He spit on his own face.

1793
02:04:33.793 --> 02:04:35.883
- [Music concludes]
- [She gasps]

1794
02:04:36.673 --> 02:04:38.503
It startled him too. and he woke up.

1795
02:04:40.093 --> 02:04:41.753
The day he came back from Daejeon?

1796
02:04:41.843 --> 02:04:43.343
"It's so unfair"?

1797
02:04:45.043 --> 02:04:48.213
As you know. Minting and Security
Printing Corp is in Daejeon.

1798
02:04:49.543 --> 02:04:51.149
[Deep exhale]

1799
02:04:51.173 --> 02:04:53.133
Was that when it started?

1800
02:04:54.753 --> 02:04:58.463
He just listened to music here.
avoided going to bed with me.

1801
02:04:59.503 --> 02:05:04.423
After he got fired.
he drank all day. developed depression.

1802
02:05:05.093 --> 02:05:06.093
Oh my god.

1803
02:05:07.593 --> 02:05:09.503
He didn't bring his medication.

1804
02:05:12.343 --> 02:05:13.343
Honey.

1805
02:05:14.253 --> 02:05:15.769
where in the world are you?

1806
02:05:15.793 --> 02:05:19.043
Does your husband own
a handgun by any chance?

1807
02:05:26.503 --> 02:05:29.173
Can I ask why you take
so long to answer?

1808
02:05:32.043 --> 02:05:35.633
If you own a firearm.
you need to report it. right?

1809
02:05:36.793 --> 02:05:37.899
He didn't do that.

1810
02:05:37.923 --> 02:05:39.173
What's more...

1811
02:05:40.753 --> 02:05:42.753
[She whispers] it vanished
with my husband.

1812
02:05:43.713 --> 02:05:45.343
He could...

1813
02:05:46.253 --> 02:05:47.713
commit suicide with it.

1814
02:05:48.673 --> 02:05:50.383
Please find him quickly.

1815
02:05:54.843 --> 02:05:56.463
[Detective] Was it one of these?

1816
02:06:14.423 --> 02:06:15.503
This one?

1817
02:06:23.503 --> 02:06:24.753
[He sighs]

1818
02:06:24.843 --> 02:06:27.843
Gu Bummo's wife really said that?

1819
02:06:30.043 --> 02:06:32.843
So be wary of Gu Bummo.

1820
02:06:33.383 --> 02:06:34.593
Remember his face.

1821
02:06:38.963 --> 02:06:43.423
Gu Bummo killed Go Sijo and ran away?

1822
02:06:45.293 --> 02:06:47.673
Wow. this is...

1823
02:06:52.673 --> 02:06:53.673
Huh.

1824
02:07:00.673 --> 02:07:01.963
<i>Honey!</i>

1825
02:07:04.883 --> 02:07:06.383
Got something to say?

1826
02:07:11.463 --> 02:07:13.383
Congrats on your first day at work.

1827
02:07:18.043 --> 02:07:20.003
This weekend. should we do a pig roast?

1828
02:07:20.093 --> 02:07:21.593
- No.
- No way!

1829
02:07:26.673 --> 02:07:30.213
It's too cold for that now.

1830
02:07:32.133 --> 02:07:36.479
Quit the clinic and take up tennis again.
I'll buy you a new racket.

1831
02:07:36.503 --> 02:07:38.503
I'm not doing that any more.

1832
02:07:39.463 --> 02:07:40.899
I'll save money.

1833
02:07:40.923 --> 02:07:42.093
[Dogs bark. whimper]

1834
02:07:45.253 --> 02:07:47.149
Si-two Ri-two. house!

1835
02:07:47.173 --> 02:07:48.343
House!

1836
02:07:48.463 --> 02:07:50.133
[Dogs pant]

1837
02:07:51.003 --> 02:07:53.293
Ri-one. come here! Don't play over there.

1838
02:07:54.293 --> 02:07:56.439
A snail! A snail!

1839
02:07:56.463 --> 02:07:58.383
I called the real estate agent.

1840
02:07:59.593 --> 02:08:01.649
Said we'll keep the house.

1841
02:08:01.673 --> 02:08:02.793
Oh.

1842
02:08:02.883 --> 02:08:06.173
[Miri] We planted an apple tree here.
how can we sell it?

1843
02:08:06.883 --> 02:08:08.173
[Man-su] Exactly.

1844
02:08:09.423 --> 02:08:10.633
Ri-one!

1845
02:08:12.253 --> 02:08:13.253
Ri-one!

1846
02:08:14.423 --> 02:08:15.963
I'll see you later.

1847
02:08:20.133 --> 02:08:23.343
Bugs are eating it alive.

1848
02:08:31.043 --> 02:08:33.519
[Newscaster on radio] <i>...will ease up
sometime this morning.</i>

1849
02:08:33.543 --> 02:08:37.189
<i>After the nighttime rain which
seemed to mourn the passing of autumn.</i>

1850
02:08:37.213 --> 02:08:41.343
<i>the temperature also dropped sharply.
bringing us one step closer to winter.</i>

1851
02:08:55.463 --> 02:08:58.253
- Going to school already?
- Dongho and I are meeting early.

1852
02:08:58.343 --> 02:09:00.939
Are you two still friends?

1853
02:09:00.963 --> 02:09:04.673
- Even after what happened last...
- [Elegant. nostalgic cello music nearby]

